WEBVTT

00:00:19.520 --> 00:00:20.100
1.

00:00:22.240 --> 00:00:27.940
For as much as many have taken in hand to set forth in order a declaration of those

00:00:27.940 --> 00:00:33.900
things which are most surely believed among us, even as they delivered them unto us, which

00:00:33.900 --> 00:00:40.500
from the beginning were eyewitnesses and ministers of the word, it seemed good to me also, having

00:00:40.500 --> 00:00:46.580
had perfect understanding of all things from the very first, to write unto thee in order,

00:00:46.800 --> 00:00:52.180
most excellent Theophilus, that thou mightest know the certainty of those things wherein

00:00:52.180 --> 00:00:53.760
thou hast been instructed.

00:00:54.620 --> 00:01:00.880
There was, in the days of Herod the king of Judea, a certain priest named Zacharias of

00:01:00.880 --> 00:01:05.700
the course of Abia, and his wife was of the daughters of Aaron, and her name was Elizabeth.

00:01:06.500 --> 00:01:12.120
And they were both righteous before God, walking in all the commandments and ordinances of

00:01:12.120 --> 00:01:13.400
the Lord blameless.

00:01:14.100 --> 00:01:20.140
And they had no child, because that Elizabeth was barren, and they both were now well stricken

00:01:20.140 --> 00:01:20.960
in years.

00:01:21.600 --> 00:01:27.680
And it came to pass, that while he executed the priest's office before God in the order

00:01:27.680 --> 00:01:33.180
of his course, according to the custom of the priest's office, his lot was to burn

00:01:33.180 --> 00:01:36.340
incense when he went into the temple of the Lord.

00:01:37.280 --> 00:01:41.580
And the whole multitude of the people were praying without at the time of incense.

00:01:42.640 --> 00:01:47.800
And there appeared unto him an angel of the Lord standing on the right side of the altar

00:01:47.800 --> 00:01:48.680
of incense.

00:01:49.400 --> 00:01:54.040
And when Zacharias saw him, he was troubled, and fear fell upon him.

00:01:54.720 --> 00:02:02.160
But the angel said unto him, Fear not, Zacharias, for thy prayer is heard, and thy wife Elizabeth

00:02:02.160 --> 00:02:06.480
shall bear thee a son, and thou shalt call his name John.

00:02:07.500 --> 00:02:12.400
And thou shalt have joy and gladness, and many shall rejoice at his birth.

00:02:13.020 --> 00:02:18.700
For he shall be great in the sight of the Lord, and shall drink neither wine nor strong

00:02:18.700 --> 00:02:23.760
drink, and he shall be filled with the Holy Ghost even from his mother's womb.

00:02:25.260 --> 00:02:29.260
And many of the children of Israel shall he turn to the Lord their God.

00:02:30.080 --> 00:02:35.820
And he shall go before him in the spirit and power of Elias to turn the hearts of the fathers

00:02:35.820 --> 00:02:41.560
to the children, and the disobedient to the wisdom of the just, to make ready a people

00:02:41.560 --> 00:02:43.180
prepared for the Lord.

00:02:44.180 --> 00:02:48.560
And Zacharias said unto the angel, Whereby shall I know this?

00:02:48.620 --> 00:02:52.660
For I am an old man, and my wife well stricken in years.

00:02:53.600 --> 00:03:00.700
And the angel answering said unto him, I am Gabriel, that stand in the presence of God,

00:03:01.040 --> 00:03:05.340
and am sent to speak unto thee, and to show thee these glad tidings.

00:03:06.880 --> 00:03:13.360
And behold, thou shalt be dumb, and not able to speak until the day that these things shall

00:03:13.360 --> 00:03:19.000
be performed, because thou believest not my words, which shall be fulfilled in their season.

00:03:19.800 --> 00:03:24.300
And the people waited for Zacharias, and marveled that he tarried so long in the temple.

00:03:25.260 --> 00:03:30.300
And when he came out, he could not speak unto them, and they perceived that he had seen

00:03:30.300 --> 00:03:34.980
a vision in the temple, for he beckoned unto them, and remained speechless.

00:03:35.700 --> 00:03:40.920
And it came to pass, that, as soon as the days of his ministration were accomplished,

00:03:41.200 --> 00:03:43.220
he departed to his own house.

00:03:43.760 --> 00:03:49.560
And after those days his wife Elizabeth conceived, and hid herself five months, saying, Thus

00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:54.640
hath the Lord dealt with me in the days wherein he looked on me, to take away my reproach

00:03:54.640 --> 00:03:55.480
among men.

00:03:56.200 --> 00:04:01.600
And in the sixth month the angel Gabriel was sent from God unto a city of Galilee,

00:04:01.920 --> 00:04:08.500
named Nazareth, to a virgin espoused to a man whose name was Joseph of the house of

00:04:08.500 --> 00:04:11.300
David, and the virgin's name was Mary.

00:04:12.140 --> 00:04:19.320
And the angel came in unto her, and said, Hail, thou that art highly favored, the Lord

00:04:19.320 --> 00:04:22.800
is with thee, blessed art thou among women.

00:04:23.700 --> 00:04:29.120
And when she saw him, she was troubled at his saying, and cast in her mind what manner

00:04:29.120 --> 00:04:31.120
of salutation this should be.

00:04:31.920 --> 00:04:37.960
And the angel said unto her, Fear not, Mary, for thou hast found favor with God.

00:04:38.700 --> 00:04:44.640
And behold, thou shalt conceive in thy womb, and bring forth a son, and shalt call his

00:04:44.640 --> 00:04:45.480
name Jesus.

00:04:46.120 --> 00:04:52.180
He shall be great, and shall be called the Son of the Highest, and the Lord God shall

00:04:52.180 --> 00:04:54.580
give unto him the throne of his father David.

00:04:55.200 --> 00:05:00.540
And he shall reign over the house of Jacob for ever, and of his kingdom there shall be

00:05:00.540 --> 00:05:01.300
no end.

00:05:02.420 --> 00:05:08.240
Then said Mary unto the angel, How shall this be, seeing I know not a man?

00:05:09.720 --> 00:05:15.560
And the angel answered and said unto her, The Holy Ghost shall come upon thee, and the

00:05:15.560 --> 00:05:17.840
power of the Highest shall overshadow thee.

00:05:17.840 --> 00:05:23.240
Therefore also that holy thing which shall be born of thee shall be called the Son of

00:05:23.240 --> 00:05:23.700
God.

00:05:24.600 --> 00:05:31.280
And behold, thy cousin Elizabeth, she hath also conceived a son in her old age, and this

00:05:31.280 --> 00:05:34.620
is the sixth month with her who was called barren.

00:05:35.040 --> 00:05:37.800
For with God nothing shall be impossible.

00:05:38.720 --> 00:05:44.480
And Mary said, Behold the handmaid of the Lord, be it unto me according to thy word.

00:05:44.880 --> 00:05:46.940
And the angel departed from her.

00:05:48.040 --> 00:05:52.520
And Mary arose in those days, and went into the hill country with haste, into a city of

00:05:52.520 --> 00:05:57.400
Judah, and entered into the house of Zacharias, and saluted Elizabeth.

00:05:58.140 --> 00:06:03.780
And it came to pass that when Elizabeth heard the salutation of Mary, the babe leaped in

00:06:03.780 --> 00:06:07.060
her womb, and Elizabeth was filled with the Holy Ghost.

00:06:07.480 --> 00:06:14.060
And she spake out with a loud voice, and said, Blessed art thou among women, and blessed

00:06:14.060 --> 00:06:19.280
is the fruit of thy womb, and whence is this to me that the mother of my Lord should come

00:06:19.280 --> 00:06:19.900
to me?

00:06:20.300 --> 00:06:26.500
For lo, as soon as the voice of thy salutation sounded in mine ears, the babe leaped in my

00:06:26.500 --> 00:06:27.440
womb for joy.

00:06:28.160 --> 00:06:32.760
And blessed is she that believed, for thou shalt be a performance of those things which

00:06:32.760 --> 00:06:34.200
were told her from the Lord.

00:06:34.880 --> 00:06:42.300
And Mary said, My soul doth magnify the Lord, and my spirit hath rejoiced in God my Saviour.

00:06:42.300 --> 00:06:45.760
For he hath regarded the low estate of his handmaiden.

00:06:46.260 --> 00:06:50.980
For behold, from henceforth all generations shall call me blessed.

00:06:52.120 --> 00:06:58.200
For he that is mighty hath done to me great things, and holy is his name.

00:06:59.340 --> 00:07:03.760
And his mercy is on them that fear him from generation to generation.

00:07:04.240 --> 00:07:06.520
He hath shewed strength with his arm.

00:07:06.940 --> 00:07:10.740
He hath scattered the proud in the imagination of their hearts.

00:07:11.160 --> 00:07:16.880
He hath put down the mighty from their seats, and exalted them of low degree.

00:07:17.140 --> 00:07:22.660
He hath filled the hungry with good things, and the rich he hath sent empty away.

00:07:23.200 --> 00:07:28.560
He hath holpen his servant Israel in remembrance of his mercy, as he spake to our fathers,

00:07:28.880 --> 00:07:31.080
to Abraham, and to his seed for ever.

00:07:31.700 --> 00:07:35.780
And Mary abode with her about three months, and returned to her own house.

00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:41.720
Now Elizabeth's full time came that she should be delivered, and she brought forth a son.

00:07:42.240 --> 00:07:46.760
And her neighbors and her cousins heard how the Lord had showed great mercy upon her,

00:07:46.920 --> 00:07:48.700
and they rejoiced with her.

00:07:48.960 --> 00:07:54.540
And it came to pass that on the eighth day they came to circumcise the child, and they

00:07:54.540 --> 00:07:57.380
called him Zacharias after the name of his father.

00:07:58.260 --> 00:08:03.540
And his mother answered and said, Not so, but he shall be called John.

00:08:04.140 --> 00:08:08.100
And they said unto her, There is none of thy kindred that is called by this name.

00:08:08.620 --> 00:08:11.820
And they made signs to his father how he would have him called.

00:08:12.660 --> 00:08:17.260
And he asked for a writing table, and wrote, saying, His name is John.

00:08:17.700 --> 00:08:19.220
And they marveled all.

00:08:19.720 --> 00:08:24.060
And his mouth was opened immediately, and his tongue loosed, and he spake and praised

00:08:24.060 --> 00:08:24.500
God.

00:08:24.880 --> 00:08:30.080
And fear came on all that dwelt round about them, and all these sayings were noised abroad

00:08:30.080 --> 00:08:32.420
throughout all the hill country of Judea.

00:08:32.420 --> 00:08:37.620
And all they that heard them laid them up in their hearts, saying, What manner of child

00:08:37.620 --> 00:08:38.640
shall this be?

00:08:39.320 --> 00:08:41.220
And the hand of the Lord was with him.

00:08:41.660 --> 00:08:47.240
And his father Zacharias was filled with the Holy Ghost, and prophesied, saying, Blessed

00:08:47.240 --> 00:08:53.860
be the Lord God of Israel, for he hath visited and redeemed his people, and hath raised up

00:08:53.860 --> 00:08:59.080
an horn of salvation for us in the house of his servant David, as he spake by the mouth

00:08:59.080 --> 00:09:04.460
of his holy prophets, which have been since the world began, that we should be saved from

00:09:04.460 --> 00:09:09.420
our enemies, and from the hand of all that hate us, to perform the mercy promised to

00:09:09.420 --> 00:09:15.060
our fathers, and to remember his holy covenant, the oath which he sware to our father Abraham,

00:09:15.940 --> 00:09:21.520
that he would grant unto us, that we being delivered out of the hand of our enemies might

00:09:21.520 --> 00:09:28.000
serve him without fear, in holiness and righteousness before him all the days of our life.

00:09:28.640 --> 00:09:34.400
And thou, child, shalt be called the prophet of the highest, for thou shalt go before the

00:09:34.400 --> 00:09:40.240
face of the Lord to prepare his ways, to give knowledge of salvation unto his people by

00:09:40.240 --> 00:09:46.780
the remission of their sins, through the tender mercy of our God, whereby the day spring

00:09:46.780 --> 00:09:52.120
from on high hath visited us, to give light to them that sit in darkness and in the shadow

00:09:52.120 --> 00:09:55.720
of death, to guide our feet into the way of peace.

00:09:56.460 --> 00:10:02.580
And the child grew and waxed strong in spirit, and was in the deserts till the day of his

00:10:02.580 --> 00:10:04.280
showing unto Israel.

00:10:07.580 --> 00:10:13.420
And it came to pass in those days, that there went out a decree from Caesar Augustus that

00:10:13.420 --> 00:10:15.540
all the world should be taxed.

00:10:15.760 --> 00:10:19.980
And this taxing was first made when Cyrenius was governor of Syria.

00:10:20.800 --> 00:10:24.760
And all went to be taxed, every one into his own city.

00:10:25.720 --> 00:10:31.720
And Joseph also went up from Galilee out of the city of Nazareth into Judea unto the city

00:10:31.720 --> 00:10:37.240
of David, which is called Bethlehem, because he was of the house and lineage of David,

00:10:37.760 --> 00:10:41.560
to be taxed with Mary his espoused wife being great with child.

00:10:42.300 --> 00:10:46.680
And so it was, that while they were there the days were accomplished that she should

00:10:47.420 --> 00:10:53.500
And she brought forth her firstborn son, and wrapped him in swaddling clothes, and laid

00:10:53.500 --> 00:10:57.180
him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn.

00:10:57.860 --> 00:11:02.780
And there were in the same country shepherds abiding in the field, keeping watch over

00:11:02.780 --> 00:11:04.000
their flock by night.

00:11:04.680 --> 00:11:05.340
And lo!

00:11:05.820 --> 00:11:10.960
the angel of the Lord came upon them, and the glory of the Lord shone round about them,

00:11:11.060 --> 00:11:12.740
and they were sore afraid.

00:11:13.600 --> 00:11:16.840
And the angel said unto them, Fear not!

00:11:17.320 --> 00:11:22.240
For behold, I bring you good tidings of great joy which shall be to all people.

00:11:22.920 --> 00:11:29.340
For unto you is born this day in the city of David a Saviour, which is Christ the Lord.

00:11:29.560 --> 00:11:32.000
And this shall be a sign unto you.

00:11:32.300 --> 00:11:36.080
Ye shall find the babe wrapped in swaddling clothes lying in a manger.

00:11:36.640 --> 00:11:42.720
And suddenly there was with the angel a multitude of the heavenly host, praising God and saying,

00:11:43.800 --> 00:11:49.000
Glory to God in the highest, and on earth peace, good will toward men.

00:11:50.160 --> 00:11:54.820
And it came to pass, as the angels were gone away from them into heaven, the shepherds

00:11:54.820 --> 00:12:00.460
said one to another, Let us now go even unto Bethlehem, and see this thing which is come

00:12:00.460 --> 00:12:04.000
to pass, which the Lord hath made known unto us.

00:12:04.660 --> 00:12:09.780
And they came with haste, and found Mary, and Joseph, and the babe lying in a manger.

00:12:10.700 --> 00:12:15.700
And when they had seen it, they made known abroad the saying which was told them concerning

00:12:15.700 --> 00:12:16.600
this child.

00:12:17.520 --> 00:12:22.040
And all they that heard it wondered at those things which were told them by the shepherds.

00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:26.320
But Mary kept all these things, and pondered them in her heart.

00:12:27.440 --> 00:12:32.040
And the shepherds returned, glorifying and praising God for all the things that they

00:12:32.040 --> 00:12:35.300
had heard and seen, as it was told unto them.

00:12:35.300 --> 00:12:40.200
And when eight days were accomplished for the circumcision of the child, his name was

00:12:40.200 --> 00:12:45.300
called Jesus, which was so named of the angel before he was conceived in the womb.

00:12:45.920 --> 00:12:50.980
And when the days of her purification according to the law of Moses were accomplished, they

00:12:50.980 --> 00:12:54.000
brought him to Jerusalem to present him to the Lord.

00:12:54.720 --> 00:13:00.760
As it is written in the law of the Lord, Every male that openeth the womb shall be called

00:13:00.760 --> 00:13:02.060
holy to the Lord.

00:13:02.740 --> 00:13:08.660
And to offer a sacrifice according to that which is said in the law of the Lord, a pair

00:13:08.660 --> 00:13:11.100
of turtle doves, or two young pigeons.

00:13:12.620 --> 00:13:16.600
And behold, there was a man in Jerusalem whose name was Simeon.

00:13:17.040 --> 00:13:22.700
And the same man was just and devout, waiting for the consolation of Israel.

00:13:23.040 --> 00:13:25.160
And the Holy Ghost was upon him.

00:13:25.460 --> 00:13:30.980
And it was revealed unto him by the Holy Ghost that he should not see death before he had

00:13:30.980 --> 00:13:32.460
seen the Lord's Christ.

00:13:33.000 --> 00:13:37.360
And he came by the Spirit into the temple, and when the parents brought in the child

00:13:37.360 --> 00:13:43.740
Jesus to do for him after the custom of the law, then took he him up in his arms and blessed

00:13:43.740 --> 00:13:44.960
God and said,

00:14:02.900 --> 00:14:07.480
And Joseph and his mother marveled at those things which were spoken of him.

00:14:08.020 --> 00:14:14.480
And Simeon blessed them, and said unto Mary his mother, Behold, this child is set for

00:14:14.480 --> 00:14:20.800
the fall and rising again of many in Israel, and for a sign which shall be spoken against.

00:14:21.520 --> 00:14:25.240
Yea, a sword shall pierce through thine own soul also.

00:14:25.240 --> 00:14:28.680
That the thoughts of many hearts may be revealed.

00:14:31.040 --> 00:14:36.700
And there was one Anna, a prophetess, the daughter of Phanuel, of the tribe of Aesir.

00:14:37.040 --> 00:14:42.240
She was of a great age, and had lived with a husband seven years from her virginity.

00:14:42.700 --> 00:14:47.980
And she was a widow of about four score and four years, which departed not from the temple

00:14:47.980 --> 00:14:51.560
but served God with fastings and prayers night and day.

00:14:52.340 --> 00:14:58.420
And she, coming in that instant, gave thanks likewise unto the Lord, and spake of him to

00:14:58.420 --> 00:15:01.140
all them that looked for redemption in Jerusalem.

00:15:01.720 --> 00:15:06.760
And when they had performed all things according to the law of the Lord, they returned into

00:15:06.760 --> 00:15:08.860
Galilee to their own city Nazareth.

00:15:09.600 --> 00:15:15.720
And the child grew and waxed strong in spirit, filled with wisdom, and the grace of God was

00:15:15.720 --> 00:15:16.480
upon him.

00:15:17.260 --> 00:15:20.980
Now his parents went to Jerusalem every year at the feast of the Passover.

00:15:21.680 --> 00:15:26.540
And when he was twelve years old, they went up to Jerusalem after the custom of the feast.

00:15:27.180 --> 00:15:32.680
And when they had fulfilled the days, as they returned, the child Jesus tarried behind in

00:15:32.680 --> 00:15:36.140
Jerusalem, and Joseph and his mother knew not of it.

00:15:37.080 --> 00:15:42.840
But they, supposing him to have been in the company, went a day's journey, and they sought

00:15:42.840 --> 00:15:45.260
him among their kinsfolk and acquaintance.

00:15:45.260 --> 00:15:49.820
And when they found him not, they turned back again to Jerusalem, seeking him.

00:15:50.400 --> 00:15:55.040
And it came to pass that after three days they found him in the temple, sitting in the

00:15:55.040 --> 00:15:59.500
midst of the doctors, both hearing them and asking them questions.

00:16:00.040 --> 00:16:04.460
And all that heard him were astonished at his understanding and answers.

00:16:05.440 --> 00:16:07.360
And when they saw him, they were amazed.

00:16:07.720 --> 00:16:12.780
And his mother said unto him, Son, why hast thou thus dealt with us?

00:16:12.780 --> 00:16:16.380
Behold, thy father and I have sought thee sorrowing.

00:16:16.820 --> 00:16:20.880
And he said unto them, How is it that ye sought me?

00:16:21.500 --> 00:16:24.740
Wisst ye not that I must be about my father's business?

00:16:25.540 --> 00:16:28.920
And they understood not the saying which he spake unto them.

00:16:29.100 --> 00:16:33.020
And he went down with them and came to Nazareth, and was subject unto them.

00:16:33.300 --> 00:16:36.100
But his mother kept all these sayings in her heart.

00:16:36.720 --> 00:16:42.320
And Jesus increased in wisdom and stature, and in favor with God and man.

00:17:06.295 --> 00:17:06.915
III.

00:17:09.215 --> 00:17:14.355
Now in the fifteenth year of the reign of Tiberius Caesar, Pontius Pilate being governor

00:17:14.355 --> 00:17:20.495
of Judea, and Herod being tetrarch of Galilee, and his brother Philip tetrarch of Ituraea,

00:17:20.675 --> 00:17:26.795
and of the region of Trachonitis, and Lysanius the tetrarch of Abilene, Anas and Caiaphas

00:17:26.795 --> 00:17:32.355
being the high priests, the word of God came unto John the son of Zacharias in the wilderness.

00:17:33.015 --> 00:17:38.095
And he came into all the country about Jordan preaching the baptism of repentance for the

00:17:38.095 --> 00:17:39.215
remission of sins.

00:17:40.065 --> 00:17:42.515
As it is written in the book of the words of

00:17:42.515 --> 00:17:47.655
Isaias the prophet, saying, The voice of one crying in the wilderness,

00:17:48.335 --> 00:17:52.875
Prepare ye the way of the Lord, make his paths straight.

00:17:53.875 --> 00:17:58.495
Every valley shall be filled, and every mountain and hill shall be brought low,

00:17:58.935 --> 00:18:03.475
And the crooked shall be made straight, and the rough ways shall be made smooth,

00:18:03.695 --> 00:18:06.415
And all flesh shall see the salvation of God.

00:18:07.135 --> 00:18:10.935
Then said he to the multitude that came forth to be baptized of him,

00:18:11.655 --> 00:18:16.495
O generation of vipers, who hath warned you to flee from the wrath to come?

00:18:17.275 --> 00:18:22.995
Bring forth therefore fruits worthy of repentance, and begin not to say within yourselves,

00:18:23.655 --> 00:18:29.555
We have Abraham to our father, for I say unto you that God is able of these stones

00:18:29.555 --> 00:18:31.515
To raise up children unto Abraham.

00:18:32.355 --> 00:18:35.975
And now also the axe is laid unto the root of the trees,

00:18:36.615 --> 00:18:41.135
Every tree therefore which bringeth not forth good fruit is hewn down,

00:18:41.555 --> 00:18:43.015
And cast into the fire.

00:18:43.755 --> 00:18:47.335
And the people asked him, saying, What shall we do then?

00:18:47.755 --> 00:18:53.235
He answereth and saith unto them, He that hath two coats, let him impart to him

00:18:53.235 --> 00:18:57.075
That hath none, and he that hath meat, let him do likewise.

00:18:57.845 --> 00:19:01.955
Then came also publicans to be baptized, and said unto him,

00:19:02.355 --> 00:19:04.695
Master, what shall we do?

00:19:05.095 --> 00:19:10.055
And he said unto them, Exact no more than that which has appointed you.

00:19:11.015 --> 00:19:15.495
And the soldiers likewise demanded of him, saying, And what shall we do?

00:19:15.715 --> 00:19:21.275
And he said unto them, Do violence to no man, neither accuse any falsely,

00:19:21.575 --> 00:19:23.615
And be content with your wages.

00:19:24.875 --> 00:19:30.095
And as the people were in expectation, and all men mused in their hearts of John

00:19:30.095 --> 00:19:34.915
Whether he were the Christ or not, John answered, saying unto them all,

00:19:35.215 --> 00:19:39.435
I indeed baptize you with water, but one mightier than I cometh,

00:19:39.875 --> 00:19:43.515
The latchet of whose shoes I am not worthy to unloose.

00:19:43.895 --> 00:19:47.755
He shall baptize you with the Holy Ghost and with fire,

00:19:48.535 --> 00:19:52.455
Whose fan is in his hand, and he will throughly purge his floor,

00:19:52.455 --> 00:19:56.495
And will gather the wheat into his garner, but the chaff he will burn

00:19:56.495 --> 00:19:58.335
With fire unquenchable.

00:19:58.955 --> 00:20:02.655
And many other things in his exhortation preached he unto the people.

00:20:04.015 --> 00:20:08.575
But Herod the Tetrarch, being reproved by him for Herodias,

00:20:08.635 --> 00:20:13.115
His brother Philip's wife, and for all the evils which Herod had done,

00:20:13.995 --> 00:20:17.535
Added yet this above all, that he shut up John in prison.

00:20:18.235 --> 00:20:22.515
Now when all the people were baptized, it came to pass that Jesus also,

00:20:22.655 --> 00:20:26.035
Being baptized and praying, the heaven was opened,

00:20:26.455 --> 00:20:31.395
And the Holy Ghost descended in a bodily shape like a dove upon him,

00:20:31.615 --> 00:20:34.055
And a voice came from heaven which said,

00:20:34.575 --> 00:20:38.815
Thou art my beloved Son, in thee I am well pleased.

00:20:40.175 --> 00:20:43.755
And Jesus himself began to be about thirty years of age,

00:20:43.755 --> 00:20:49.535
Being, as was supposed, the son of Joseph, which was the son of Heli,

00:20:49.895 --> 00:20:52.795
Which was the son of Methat, which was the son of Levi,

00:20:53.335 --> 00:20:56.775
Which was the son of Melchai, which was the son of Janna,

00:20:57.095 --> 00:21:01.055
Which was the son of Joseph, which was the son of Mountathias,

00:21:01.255 --> 00:21:04.155
Which was the son of Amos, which was the son of Naum,

00:21:04.615 --> 00:21:09.035
Which was the son of Ezli, which was the son of Negei,

00:21:09.035 --> 00:21:12.915
Which was the son of Meath, which was the son of Mountithias,

00:21:12.915 --> 00:21:18.635
which was the son of Simei which was the son of Joseph, which was the son of Judah

00:21:18.635 --> 00:21:24.335
which was the son of Joan which was the son of Risa which was the son of Zorah Babel

00:21:24.735 --> 00:21:28.815
which was the son of Silatheal which was the son of neirai

00:21:29.995 --> 00:21:35.575
which was the son of Melkai which was the son of Adai which was the son of Kosem

00:21:35.575 --> 00:21:39.835
which was the son of Elmodam which was the son of Er

00:21:40.415 --> 00:21:45.435
Which was the son of Josiah, which was the son of Eliezer, which was the son

00:21:45.435 --> 00:21:51.775
of Joram, which was the son of Mawthat, which was the son of Levi, which was the

00:21:51.775 --> 00:21:56.215
son of Simeon, which was the son of Judah, which was the son of Joseph, which

00:21:56.215 --> 00:22:02.455
was the son of Jonan, which was the son of Eliakim, which was the son of Malaeh,

00:22:02.795 --> 00:22:07.895
which was the son of Menun, which was the son of Mattatha, which was the son of

00:22:07.895 --> 00:22:13.875
Nathan which was the son of David, which was the son of Jesse which was the son of Obed

00:22:13.875 --> 00:22:19.995
which was the son of Boaz which was the son of Salmon which was the the son of Na Large

00:22:19.995 --> 00:22:27.295
which was the son of Amenadab which was the son of Aram which was the son of Esraam which

00:22:27.295 --> 00:22:33.575
was the son of Phares which was the son of Judah which was the Son of Jacob which was

00:22:33.575 --> 00:22:39.595
son of Isaac, which was the son of Abraham, which was the son of Thera, which

00:22:39.595 --> 00:22:45.435
was the son of Nakor, which was the son of Saruk, which was the son of Raegaw,

00:22:45.775 --> 00:22:50.995
which was the son of Phalech, which was the son of Heber, which was the son of

00:22:50.995 --> 00:22:57.615
Salah, which was the son of Kainin, which was the son of Arphaxad, which was the

00:22:57.615 --> 00:23:05.195
of Sem, which was the son of Noah, which was the son of Lesmik, which was the son of Methuselah,

00:23:05.375 --> 00:23:10.815
which was the son of Enoch, which was the son of Jared, which was the son of M container,

00:23:11.335 --> 00:23:17.235
which was the son of Kaim That is, which was the son of Einus, which was the son of Seth,

00:23:17.755 --> 00:23:22.135
which was the son of Adam, which was the son of God.

00:23:24.135 --> 00:23:31.275
4. And Jesus, being full of the Holy Ghost, returned from Jordan, and was led by the Spirit

00:23:31.275 --> 00:23:37.575
into the wilderness, being forty days tempted of the devil. And in those days he did eat

00:23:37.575 --> 00:23:43.735
nothing, and when they were ended he afterward hungered. And the devil said unto him, If

00:23:43.735 --> 00:23:49.935
thou be the Son of God, command this stone, that it be made bread. And Jesus answered

00:23:49.935 --> 00:23:55.935
him, saying, It is written, that man shall not live by bread alone, but by every word

00:23:55.935 --> 00:24:03.555
of God. And the devil, taking him up into an high mountain, showed unto him all the

00:24:03.555 --> 00:24:09.955
kingdoms of the world in a moment of time. And the devil said unto him, All this power

00:24:09.955 --> 00:24:16.415
will I give thee, and the glory of them, for that is delivered unto me, and to whomsoever

00:24:16.415 --> 00:24:24.935
I will I give it. If thou therefore wilt worship me, all shall be thine. And Jesus answered

00:24:24.935 --> 00:24:30.235
and said unto him, Get thee behind me, Satan, for it is written, Thou shalt worship the

00:24:30.235 --> 00:24:36.835
Lord thy God, and him only shalt thou serve. And he brought him to Jerusalem, and said

00:24:36.835 --> 00:24:42.555
him on a pinnacle of the temple, and said unto him, If thou be the Son of God, cast

00:24:42.555 --> 00:24:49.035
thyself down from hence. For it is written, He shall give his angels charge over thee

00:24:49.035 --> 00:24:55.175
to keep thee, and in their hands they shall bear thee up, lest at any time thou dash thy

00:24:55.175 --> 00:25:01.795
foot against a stone. And Jesus answering said unto him, It is said, Thou shalt not

00:25:01.795 --> 00:25:08.055
tempt the Lord thy God. And when the devil had ended all the temptation, he departed from

00:25:08.055 --> 00:25:16.295
him for a season. And Jesus returned in the power of the Spirit into Galilee. And there

00:25:16.295 --> 00:25:22.295
went out a fame of him through all the region round about, and he taught in their synagogues,

00:25:22.415 --> 00:25:29.355
being glorified of all. And he came to Nazareth where he had been brought up, and as his custom

00:25:29.355 --> 00:25:35.655
was, he went into the synagogue on the Sabbath day, and stood up for to read. And there was

00:25:35.655 --> 00:25:41.115
delivered unto him the book of the prophet Isaiah. And when he had opened the book, he

00:25:41.115 --> 00:25:46.975
found the place where it was written. The Spirit of the Lord is upon me, because he

00:25:46.975 --> 00:25:52.775
hath anointed me to preach the gospel to the poor. He hath sent me to heal the brokenhearted,

00:25:53.335 --> 00:25:58.815
to preach deliverance to the captives, and recovering of sight to the blind, to set at

00:25:58.815 --> 00:26:05.635
liberty them that are bruised, to preach the acceptable year of the Lord. And he closed

00:26:05.635 --> 00:26:11.615
the book, and he gave it again to the minister, and sat down. And the eyes of all them that

00:26:11.615 --> 00:26:18.735
were in the synagogue were fastened on him. And he began to say unto them, This day is

00:26:18.735 --> 00:26:25.155
this scripture fulfilled in your ears. And all bare him witness, and wondered at the

00:26:25.155 --> 00:26:31.935
gracious words which proceeded out of his mouth. And they said, Is not this Joseph's

00:26:31.935 --> 00:26:39.515
son? And he said unto them, Ye will surely say unto me this proverb, Physician, heal

00:26:39.515 --> 00:26:47.375
thyself. Whatsoever we have heard done in Capernaum, do also hear in thy country. And he said,

00:26:48.155 --> 00:26:56.235
Verily I say unto you, No prophet is accepted in his own country. But I tell you of a truth,

00:26:56.815 --> 00:27:01.995
Many widows were in Israel in the days of Elias, when the heaven was shut up three years

00:27:01.995 --> 00:27:09.415
and six months, when great famine was throughout all the land. But unto none of them was Elias

00:27:09.415 --> 00:27:16.515
sent save unto Serepta, a city of Sidon, unto a woman that was a widow. And many lepers

00:27:16.515 --> 00:27:22.295
were in Israel in the time of Elishaias the prophet. And none of them was cleansed, saving

00:27:22.295 --> 00:27:28.895
Naaman the Syrian. And all they in the synagogue when they heard these things were filled

00:27:28.895 --> 00:27:35.255
with wrath, and rose up and thrust him out of the city, and led him unto the brow of

00:27:35.255 --> 00:27:41.995
the hill whereon their city was built, that they might cast him down headlong. But he

00:27:41.995 --> 00:27:48.115
passing through the midst of them went his way, and came down to Capernaum a city of

00:27:48.115 --> 00:27:56.095
them on the Sabbath days. And they were astonished at his doctrine, for his word was with power.

00:27:56.835 --> 00:28:02.275
And in the synagogue there was a man which had a spirit of an unclean devil, and cried

00:28:02.275 --> 00:28:08.235
out with a loud voice, saying, Let us alone. What have we to do with thee, thou Jesus of

00:28:08.235 --> 00:28:14.775
Nazareth? Art thou come to destroy us? I know thee, who thou art, the Holy One of God.

00:28:15.625 --> 00:28:22.695
And Jesus rebuked him, saying, Hold thy peace, and come out of him. And when the devil had

00:28:22.695 --> 00:28:28.975
thrown him in the midst, he came out of him, and hurt him not. And they were all amazed

00:28:28.975 --> 00:28:35.295
and spake among themselves, saying, What a word is this? For with authority and power

00:28:35.295 --> 00:28:41.515
he commandeth the unclean spirits, and they come out. And the fame of him went out into

00:28:41.515 --> 00:28:47.675
every place of the country round about. And he arose out of the synagogue, and entered

00:28:47.675 --> 00:28:54.555
into Simon's house. And Simon's wife's mother was taken with a great fever, and they

00:28:54.555 --> 00:29:00.735
besought him for her. And he stood over her, and rebuked the fever, and it left her, and

00:29:00.735 --> 00:29:07.395
immediately she arose and ministered unto them. Now when the sun was setting, all they

00:29:07.395 --> 00:29:14.055
that had any sick with diverse diseases brought them unto him. And he laid his hands on every

00:29:14.055 --> 00:29:20.935
one of them, and healed them. And devils also came out of many, crying out, and saying,

00:29:21.415 --> 00:29:28.455
Thou art Christ, the Son of God. And he rebuking them, suffered them not to speak, for they

00:29:28.455 --> 00:29:34.215
knew that he was Christ. And when it was day, he departed, and went into a desert place.

00:29:34.575 --> 00:29:39.795
And the people sought him, and came unto him, and stayed him, that he should not depart

00:29:39.795 --> 00:29:47.375
from them. And he said unto them, I must preach the kingdom of God to other cities also, for

00:29:47.375 --> 00:29:53.255
therefore am I sent. And he preached in the synagogues of Galilee.

00:30:19.284 --> 00:30:26.504
V. And it came to pass, that as the people pressed upon him to hear the word of God,

00:30:26.504 --> 00:30:35.984
he stood by the lake of Jenesseret, and saw two ships standing by the lake, but the fishermen were gone out of them and were washing their nets.

00:30:36.784 --> 00:30:47.084
And he entered into one of the ships, which was Simon's, and prayed him that he would thrust out a little from the land, and he sat down and taught the people out of the ship.

00:30:47.764 --> 00:30:55.084
Now when he had left speaking, he said unto Simon, Launch out into the deep, and let down your nets for a draft.

00:30:56.324 --> 00:31:05.544
And Simon answering said unto him, Master, we have toiled all the night, and have taken nothing. Nevertheless, at thy word, I will let down the net.

00:31:06.684 --> 00:31:18.464
And when they had done this, they enclosed a great multitude of fishes and their net break, and they beckoned unto their partners, which were in the other ship, that they should come and help them.

00:31:18.584 --> 00:31:30.684
And they came and filled both the ships, so that they began to sink. When Simon Peter saw it, he fell down at Jesus's knees, saying, Depart from me, for I am a sinful man, O Lord.

00:31:30.684 --> 00:31:36.484
For he was astonished at all that were with him at the draft of the fishes which they had taken.

00:31:37.284 --> 00:31:42.724
And so was also James and John, the sons of Zebedee, which were partners with Simon.

00:31:43.364 --> 00:31:49.164
And Jesus said unto Simon, Fear not, from henceforth thou shalt catch men.

00:31:49.924 --> 00:31:54.464
And when they had brought their ships to land, they forsook all and followed him.

00:31:54.464 --> 00:32:07.524
And it came to pass, when he was in a certain city, behold a man full of leprosy, who, seeing Jesus, fell on his face, and besought him, saying, Lord, if thou wilt, thou canst make me clean.

00:32:08.124 --> 00:32:16.744
And he put forth his hand, and touched him, saying, I will, be thou clean. And immediately the leprosy departed from him.

00:32:17.244 --> 00:32:27.104
And he charged him to tell no man, but go and show thyself to the priest, and offer for thy cleansing, according as Moses commanded, for a testimony unto them.

00:32:27.784 --> 00:32:37.924
But so much the more went there of fame abroad of him, and great multitudes came together to hear, and to be healed by him of their infirmities.

00:32:38.524 --> 00:32:41.584
And he withdrew himself into the wilderness, and prayed.

00:32:42.844 --> 00:32:54.284
And it came to pass, on a certain day, as he was teaching, that there were Pharisees and doctors of the law sitting by, which were come out of every town of Galilee, and Judea, and Jerusalem.

00:32:54.284 --> 00:32:57.864
And the power of the Lord was present to heal them.

00:32:59.044 --> 00:33:07.404
And behold, men brought in a bed a man which was taken with a palsy, and they sought means to bring him in, and to lay him before him.

00:33:08.024 --> 00:33:19.244
And when they could not find by what way they might bring him in because of the multitude, they went upon the housetop, and let him down through the tiling with his couch into the midst before Jesus.

00:33:19.244 --> 00:33:25.564
And when he saw their faith, he said unto them, Man, thy sins are forgiven thee.

00:33:26.224 --> 00:33:36.464
And the scribes and the Pharisees began to reason, saying, Who is this which speaketh blasphemies? Who can forgive sins but God alone?

00:33:37.244 --> 00:33:43.424
But when Jesus perceived their thoughts, he answering said unto them, What reason ye in your hearts?

00:33:43.424 --> 00:33:55.684
Whether is easier to say, Thy sins be forgiven thee, or to say, Rise up and walk, but that ye may know that the Son of Man hath power upon earth to forgive sins.

00:33:56.504 --> 00:34:04.824
He said unto the sick of the palsy, I say unto thee, Arise, and take up thy couch, and go into thine house.

00:34:05.464 --> 00:34:12.564
And immediately he rose up before them, and took up that whereon he lay, and departed to his own house, glorifying God.

00:34:13.164 --> 00:34:20.404
And they were all amazed, and they glorified God, and were filled with fear, saying, We have seen strange things today.

00:34:21.344 --> 00:34:29.884
And after these things he went forth, and saw a publican named Levi, sitting at the receipt of custom, and he said unto him, Follow me.

00:34:29.884 --> 00:34:41.924
And he left all, rose up, and followed him. And Levi made him a great feast in his own house, and there was a great company of publicans and of others that sat down with them.

00:34:42.504 --> 00:34:50.444
But their scribes and Pharisees murmured against his disciples, saying, Why do ye eat and drink with publicans and sinners?

00:34:51.604 --> 00:34:58.944
And Jesus answering said unto them, They that are whole need not a physician, but they that are sick.

00:34:58.944 --> 00:35:03.884
I came not to call the righteous, but sinners to repentance.

00:35:04.764 --> 00:35:13.924
And they said unto him, Why do the disciples of John fast often, and make prayers, and likewise the disciples of the Pharisees, but thine eat and drink?

00:35:14.824 --> 00:35:21.324
And he said unto them, Can ye make the children of the bride chamber fast, while the bridegroom is with them?

00:35:21.864 --> 00:35:27.684
But the days will come when the bridegroom shall be taken away from them, and then shall they fast in those days.

00:35:28.464 --> 00:35:31.724
And he spake also a parable unto them.

00:35:32.484 --> 00:35:42.684
No man putteth a piece of a new garment upon an old. If otherwise, then both the new maketh a rent, and the piece that was taken out of the new agreeeth not with the old.

00:35:43.404 --> 00:35:51.024
And no man putteth new wine into old bottles, else the new wine will burst the bottles, and be spilled, and the bottles shall perish.

00:35:51.624 --> 00:35:55.684
But new wine must be put into new bottles, and both are preserved.

00:35:55.684 --> 00:36:04.484
No man also having drunk old wine, straightway desireth new, for he saith, The old is better.

00:36:06.824 --> 00:36:16.964
And it came to pass on the second Sabbath after the first, that he went through the cornfields, and his disciples plucked the ears of corn, and did eat, rubbing them in their hands.

00:36:17.724 --> 00:36:24.204
And certain of the Pharisees said unto them, Why do ye that which is not lawful to do on the Sabbath days?

00:36:24.884 --> 00:36:34.524
And Jesus answering them said, Have ye not read so much as this what David did when himself was unhungred, and they which were with him?

00:36:34.844 --> 00:36:44.444
How he went into the house of God, and did take and eat the shoe-bread, and gave also to them that were with him, which it is not lawful to eat, but for the priests alone.

00:36:45.204 --> 00:36:50.204
And he said unto them, That the Son of man is Lord also of the Sabbath.

00:36:50.204 --> 00:36:55.964
And it came to pass also on another Sabbath that he entered into the synagogue and taught.

00:36:56.544 --> 00:36:58.964
And there was a man whose right hand was withered.

00:36:59.624 --> 00:37:07.924
And the scribes and Pharisees watched him, whether he would heal on the Sabbath day, that they might find an accusation against him.

00:37:08.384 --> 00:37:15.524
But he knew their thoughts, and said to the man which had the withered hand, Rise up and stand forth in the midst.

00:37:16.224 --> 00:37:18.084
And he arose and stood forth.

00:37:19.324 --> 00:37:23.384
Then said Jesus unto them, I will ask you one thing.

00:37:23.784 --> 00:37:29.804
Is it lawful on the Sabbath days to do good, or to do evil, to save life, or to destroy it?

00:37:30.324 --> 00:37:35.344
And looking round about upon them all, he said unto the man, Stretch forth thy hand.

00:37:35.684 --> 00:37:39.864
And he did so, and his hand was restored whole as the other.

00:37:40.544 --> 00:37:46.064
And they were filled with madness, and communed one with another what they might do to Jesus.

00:37:46.064 --> 00:37:53.244
And it came to pass in those days that he went out into a mountain to pray, and continued all night in prayer to God.

00:37:53.944 --> 00:38:00.144
And when it was day, he called unto him his disciples, and of them he chose twelve, whom also he named apostles.

00:38:01.664 --> 00:38:11.884
Simon, whom he also named Peter, and Andrew his brother, James and John, Philip and Bartholomew, Matthew and Thomas,

00:38:12.544 --> 00:38:23.084
James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon called Zalotes, and Judas the brother of James, and Judas Iscariot, which also was the traitor.

00:38:23.864 --> 00:38:30.664
And he came down with them, and stood in the plain, and the company of his disciples, and a great multitude of people,

00:38:31.024 --> 00:38:39.484
out of all Judea and Jerusalem, and from the sea coast of Tyre and Sidon, which came to hear him, and to be healed of their diseases.

00:38:39.484 --> 00:38:44.144
And they that were vexed with unclean spirits, and they were healed.

00:38:44.984 --> 00:38:49.984
And the whole multitude sought to touch him, for there went virtue out of him, and healed them all.

00:38:50.544 --> 00:38:58.564
And he lifted up his eyes on his disciples, and said, Blessed be ye poor, for yours is the kingdom of God.

00:38:59.584 --> 00:39:06.944
Blessed are ye that hunger now, for ye shall be filled. Blessed are ye that weep now, for ye shall laugh.

00:39:07.724 --> 00:39:14.824
Blessed are ye when men shall hate you, and when they shall separate you from their company, and shall reproach you,

00:39:15.124 --> 00:39:22.824
and cast out your name as evil, for the son of man's sake. Rejoice ye in that day, and leap for joy.

00:39:23.284 --> 00:39:29.564
For behold, your reward is great in heaven, for in the like manner did their fathers unto the prophets.

00:39:29.564 --> 00:39:38.724
But woe unto you that are rich, for ye have received your consolation. Woe unto you that are full, for ye shall hunger.

00:39:39.524 --> 00:39:47.024
Woe unto you that laugh now, for ye shall mourn and weep. Woe unto you when all men shall speak well of you,

00:39:47.244 --> 00:39:53.964
for so did their fathers to the false prophets. But I say unto you which hear, Love your enemies,

00:39:53.964 --> 00:40:02.544
do good to them which hate you, bless them that curse you, and pray for them which despitefully use you.

00:40:03.304 --> 00:40:12.704
And unto him that smiteth thee on the one cheek, offer also the other. And him that taketh away thy cloak, forbid not to take thy coat also.

00:40:14.044 --> 00:40:19.904
Give to every man that asketh of thee, and of him that taketh away thy goods, ask them not again.

00:40:19.904 --> 00:40:29.404
And as ye would that men should do to you, do ye also to them likewise. For if ye love them which love you, what thank have ye?

00:40:29.564 --> 00:40:36.144
For sinners also love those that love them. And if ye do good to them which do good to you, what thank have ye?

00:40:36.184 --> 00:40:43.464
For sinners also do even the same. And if ye lend to them of whom ye hope to receive, what thank have ye?

00:40:43.464 --> 00:40:51.844
For sinners also lend to sinners to receive as much again. But love ye your enemies, and do good, and lend.

00:40:52.344 --> 00:41:01.804
Hoping for nothing again, and your reward shall be great. And ye shall be the children of the highest, for he is kind unto the unthankful and to the evil.

00:41:02.744 --> 00:41:10.664
Be ye therefore merciful, as your Father also is merciful. Judge not, and ye shall not be judged.

00:41:11.384 --> 00:41:17.744
Condemn not, and ye shall not be condemned. Forgive, and ye shall be forgiven.

00:41:18.704 --> 00:41:27.384
Give, and it shall be given unto you, good measure, pressed down, and shaken together, and running over, shall men give into your bosom.

00:41:27.384 --> 00:41:32.784
For with the same measure that ye meet withal, it shall be measured to you again.

00:41:33.764 --> 00:41:41.164
And he spake a parable unto them. Can the blind lead the blind? Shall they not both fall into the ditch?

00:41:41.904 --> 00:41:47.904
The disciple is not above his master, but every one that is perfect shall be as his master.

00:41:47.904 --> 00:41:57.124
And why beholdest thou the mote that is in thy brother's eye, but perceivest not the beam that is in thine own eye?

00:41:58.604 --> 00:42:10.624
Either how canst thou say to thy brother, Brother, let me pull out the mote that is in thine eye, when thou thyself beholdest not the beam that is in thine own eye.

00:42:10.624 --> 00:42:21.164
Thou hypocrite, cast out first the beam out of thine own eye, and then shalt thou see clearly to pull out the mote that is in thy brother's eye.

00:42:21.924 --> 00:42:28.584
For a good tree bringeth not forth corrupt fruit, neither doth a corrupt tree bring forth good fruit.

00:42:29.244 --> 00:42:37.664
For every tree is known by his own fruit. For of thorns men do not gather figs, nor of a bramble bush gather they grapes.

00:42:38.504 --> 00:42:48.804
A good man out of the good treasure of his heart bringeth forth that which is good, and an evil man out of the evil treasure of his heart bringeth forth that which is evil.

00:42:49.704 --> 00:42:53.144
For of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaketh.

00:42:53.904 --> 00:43:06.484
And why call ye me, Lord, Lord, and do not the things which I say? Whosoever cometh to me, and heareth my sayings, and doeth them, I will show you to whom he is like.

00:43:06.484 --> 00:43:21.964
He is like a man which built an house and digged deep and laid the foundation on a rock, and when the flood arose the stream beat vehemently upon that house and could not shake it, for it was founded upon a rock.

00:43:21.964 --> 00:43:38.764
But he that heareth and doeth not is like a man that without a foundation built an house upon the earth, against which the stream did beat vehemently, and immediately it fell, and the ruin of that house was great.

00:43:59.918 --> 00:44:17.898
7. Now when he had ended all his sayings, in the audience of the people he entered into

00:44:17.898 --> 00:44:23.598
Capernaum. And a certain centurion servant, who was dear unto him, was sick, and ready

00:44:23.598 --> 00:44:29.278
to die. And when he heard of Jesus, he sent unto him the elders of the Jews, beseeching

00:44:29.278 --> 00:44:33.918
him that he would come and heal his servant. And when they came to Jesus, they besought

00:44:33.918 --> 00:44:39.618
him instantly, saying, That he was worthy for whom he should do this, for he loveth

00:44:39.618 --> 00:44:45.538
our nation, and he hath built us a synagogue. Then Jesus went with them, and when he was

00:44:45.538 --> 00:44:51.778
far from the house, the centurion sent friends to him, saying unto him, Lord, trouble not

00:44:51.778 --> 00:44:57.878
thyself, for I am not worthy that thou shouldest enter under my roof. Wherefore neither thought

00:44:57.878 --> 00:45:03.758
I myself worthy to come unto thee, but say in a word, and my servant shall be healed.

00:45:04.638 --> 00:45:10.818
For I also am a man set under authority, having under me soldiers, and I say unto one, Go,

00:45:10.818 --> 00:45:16.938
and he goeth, and to another, Come, and he cometh, and to my servant do this, and he

00:45:16.938 --> 00:45:21.958
doeth it. When Jesus heard these things, he marveled at him, and turned him about, and

00:45:21.958 --> 00:45:27.818
said unto the people that followed him, I say unto you, I have not found so great faith,

00:45:28.098 --> 00:45:33.738
no, not in Israel. And they that were sent, returning to the house, found the servant

00:45:33.738 --> 00:45:39.758
whole that had been sick. And it came to pass the day after that he went into a city called

00:45:39.758 --> 00:45:45.838
Nain, and many of his disciples went with him, and much people. Now when he came nigh to the

00:45:45.838 --> 00:45:51.378
gate of the city, behold, there was a dead man carried out, the only son of his mother,

00:45:51.638 --> 00:45:57.578
and she was a widow, and much people of the city was with her. And when the Lord saw her,

00:45:57.578 --> 00:46:04.558
he had compassion on her, and said unto her, Weep not. And he came and touched the beer,

00:46:04.558 --> 00:46:11.178
and they that bear him stood still. And he said, Young man, I say unto thee, Arise. And he that

00:46:11.178 --> 00:46:17.638
was dead sat up, and began to speak. And he delivered him to his mother. And there came a

00:46:17.638 --> 00:46:23.418
fear on all, and they glorified God, saying, That a great prophet is risen up among us,

00:46:23.438 --> 00:46:29.698
and that God hath visited his people. And this rumor of him went forth throughout all Judea,

00:46:29.698 --> 00:46:35.918
and throughout all the region round about. And the disciples of John showed him of all these

00:46:35.918 --> 00:46:42.478
things. And John, calling unto him two of his disciples, sent them to Jesus, saying, Art thou

00:46:42.478 --> 00:46:48.318
he that should come, or look we for another? When the men were coming to him, they said, John

00:46:48.318 --> 00:46:54.638
Baptist hath sent us unto thee, saying, Art thou he that should come, or look we for another?

00:46:55.278 --> 00:47:00.758
And in that same hour he cured many of their infirmities and plagues, and of evil spirits,

00:47:01.138 --> 00:47:06.898
and unto many that were blind he gave sight. Then Jesus answering said unto them, Go your way,

00:47:06.978 --> 00:47:12.178
and tell John what things ye have seen and heard. How that the blind see, the lame walk,

00:47:12.238 --> 00:47:18.638
the lepers are cleansed, the deaf hear, the dead are raised, to the poor the gospel is preached.

00:47:19.138 --> 00:47:22.798
And blessed is he whosoever shall not be offended in me.

00:47:23.598 --> 00:47:29.438
And when the messengers of John were departed, he began to speak unto the people concerning John.

00:47:29.998 --> 00:47:34.718
What went ye out into the wilderness for to see, a reed shaken with the wind?

00:47:35.358 --> 00:47:43.078
But what went ye out for to see, a man clothed in soft raiment? Behold, they which are gorgeously

00:47:43.078 --> 00:47:50.178
appareled and live delicately, are in king's courts. But what went ye out for to see, a prophet?

00:47:50.898 --> 00:47:56.658
Yea, I say unto you, and much more than a prophet. This is he of whom it is written,

00:47:57.298 --> 00:48:02.958
Behold, I send my messenger before thy face, which shall prepare thy way before thee.

00:48:03.638 --> 00:48:08.938
For I say unto you, among those that are born of women, there is not a greater prophet than John

00:48:08.938 --> 00:48:13.638
the Baptist. But he that is least in the kingdom of God is greater than he.

00:48:14.418 --> 00:48:19.258
And all the people that heard him and the publicans justified God being baptized with

00:48:19.258 --> 00:48:25.018
the baptism of John. But the Pharisees and lawyers rejected the counsel of God against themselves

00:48:25.018 --> 00:48:31.718
being not baptized of him. And the Lord said, Whereunto then shall I liken the men of this

00:48:31.718 --> 00:48:37.178
generation? And to what are they like? They are likened to children sitting in the marketplace

00:48:37.178 --> 00:48:43.038
and calling one to another and saying, We have piped unto you, and ye have not danced.

00:48:43.518 --> 00:48:49.938
We have mourned to you, and ye have not wept. For John the Baptist came neither eating bread

00:48:49.938 --> 00:48:56.518
nor drinking wine, and ye say, He hath a devil. The Son of Man is come eating and drinking,

00:48:56.658 --> 00:49:02.558
and ye say, Behold, a gluttonous man and a wine-bibber, a friend of publicans and sinners.

00:49:03.198 --> 00:49:09.098
But wisdom is justified of all her children. And one of the Pharisees desired him that he

00:49:09.098 --> 00:49:13.658
would eat with him, and he went into the Pharisee's house and sat down to meet.

00:49:14.378 --> 00:49:20.938
And behold, a woman in the city, which was a sinner, when she knew that Jesus sat at meat

00:49:20.938 --> 00:49:27.898
in the Pharisee's house, brought an alabaster box of ointment, and stood at his feet behind him

00:49:28.698 --> 00:49:33.518
and began to wash his feet with tears, and did wipe them with the hairs of her head,

00:49:33.958 --> 00:49:41.218
and kissed his feet, and anointed them with the ointment. Now when the Pharisee which had

00:49:41.218 --> 00:49:46.878
bidden him saw it, he spake within himself, saying, This man, if he were a prophet,

00:49:47.298 --> 00:49:54.058
would have known who and what manner of woman this is that toucheth him, for she is a sinner.

00:49:54.858 --> 00:49:59.478
And Jesus answering said unto him, Simon, I have somewhat to say unto thee,

00:49:59.798 --> 00:50:06.118
and he sayeth, Master, say on. There was a certain creditor which had two debtors,

00:50:06.278 --> 00:50:11.898
the one owed five hundred pence and the other fifty, and when they had nothing to pay he

00:50:11.898 --> 00:50:19.058
frankly forgave them both. Tell me therefore which of them will love him most. Simon answered and

00:50:19.058 --> 00:50:26.418
said, I suppose that he to whom he forgave most. And he said unto him, Thou hast rightly judged.

00:50:26.898 --> 00:50:33.018
And he turned to the woman and said unto Simon, Seest thou this woman? I entered into thine house,

00:50:33.378 --> 00:50:39.638
thou gavest me no water for my feet. But she hath washed my feet with tears and wiped them

00:50:39.638 --> 00:50:44.998
with the hairs of her head. Thou gavest me no kiss, but this woman since the time I came in

00:50:44.998 --> 00:50:51.838
hath not ceased to kiss my feet. My head with oil thou didst not anoint, but this woman hath

00:50:51.838 --> 00:50:58.758
anointed my feet with ointment. Wherefore I say unto thee, Her sins which are many are forgiven,

00:50:59.298 --> 00:51:06.598
for she loved much, but to whom little is forgiven the same loveth little. And he said unto her,

00:51:06.638 --> 00:51:12.238
Thy sins are forgiven. And they that sat at meet with him began to say within themselves,

00:51:12.238 --> 00:51:22.738
Who is this that forgiveth sins also? And he said to the woman, Thy faith hath saved thee. Go in

00:51:22.738 --> 00:51:30.638
peace. And it came to pass afterward that he went throughout every city and village

00:51:30.638 --> 00:51:35.818
preaching and showing the glad tidings of the kingdom of God, and the twelve were with him.

00:51:36.488 --> 00:51:42.298
And certain women which had been healed of evil spirits and infirmities, Mary called Magdalene,

00:51:42.998 --> 00:51:50.238
out of whom went seven devils, and Joanna, the wife of Chusa, Herod's steward, and Susanna,

00:51:50.318 --> 00:51:56.518
and many others, which ministered unto him of their substance. And when much people were gathered

00:51:56.518 --> 00:52:04.618
together and were come to him out of every city, he spake by a parable. A sower went out to sow his

00:52:04.618 --> 00:52:10.798
seed, and as he sowed, some fell by the wayside, and it was trodden down, and the fowls of the air

00:52:10.798 --> 00:52:17.298
devoured it. And some fell upon a rock, and as soon as it was sprung up it withered away because

00:52:17.298 --> 00:52:23.908
it lacked moisture. And some fell among thorns, and the thorns sprang up with it and choked it.

00:52:24.578 --> 00:52:30.838
And other fell on good ground and sprang up and bare fruit and hundredfold. And when he had said

00:52:30.838 --> 00:52:38.898
these things, he cried, He that hath ears to hear, let him hear. And his disciples asked him saying,

00:52:39.198 --> 00:52:45.978
What might this parable be? And he said, Unto you it is given to know the mysteries of the kingdom

00:52:45.978 --> 00:52:53.498
of God, but to others in parables, that seeing they might not see, and hearing they might not

00:52:53.498 --> 00:53:02.238
understand. Now the parable is this, The seed is the word of God. Those by the wayside are they that

00:53:02.238 --> 00:53:08.538
hear, then cometh the devil and taketh away the word out of their hearts, lest they should believe

00:53:08.538 --> 00:53:16.038
and be saved. They on the rock are they which, when they hear, receive the word with joy, and these

00:53:16.038 --> 00:53:23.238
have no root, which for a while believe and in time of temptation fall away. And that which fell

00:53:23.238 --> 00:53:30.158
among thorns are they which, when they have heard, go forth and are choked with cares and riches

00:53:30.158 --> 00:53:37.618
and pleasures of this life, and bring no fruit to perfection. But that on the good ground are they

00:53:37.618 --> 00:53:43.958
which, in an honest and good heart, having heard the word, keep it and bring forth fruit with

00:53:43.958 --> 00:53:52.138
patience. No man when he hath lighted a candle covereth it with a vessel, or putteth it under

00:53:52.138 --> 00:53:59.738
a bed, but setteth it on a candlestick, that they which enter in may see the light. For nothing is

00:53:59.738 --> 00:54:06.698
secret that shall not be made manifest, neither anything hid that shall not be known and come

00:54:06.698 --> 00:54:15.238
abroad. Take heed therefore how ye hear, for whosoever hath to him shall be given, and whosoever

00:54:15.238 --> 00:54:23.298
hath not from him shall be taken even that which he seemeth to have. Then came to him his mother

00:54:23.298 --> 00:54:28.758
and his brethren, and could not come at him for the press. And it was told him by certain which

00:54:28.758 --> 00:54:34.558
said, Thy mother and thy brethren stand without, desiring to see thee. And he answered and said

00:54:34.558 --> 00:54:42.378
unto them, My mother and my brethren are these which hear the word of God, and do it. Now it

00:54:42.378 --> 00:54:47.178
came to pass on a certain day that he went into a ship with his disciples, and he said unto them,

00:54:47.638 --> 00:54:54.198
Let us go over unto the other side of the lake. And they launched forth. But as they sailed he

00:54:54.198 --> 00:54:59.218
fell asleep, and there came down a storm of wind on the lake, and they were filled with water

00:54:59.218 --> 00:55:06.318
and were in jeopardy. And when they came to him and awoke him saying, Master, Master, we perish!

00:55:06.958 --> 00:55:12.358
Then he arose and rebuked the wind and the raging of the water, and they ceased, and there was a

00:55:12.358 --> 00:55:19.618
calm. And he said unto them, Where is your faith? And they, being afraid, wondered, saying one to

00:55:19.618 --> 00:55:26.878
another, What manner of man is this? for he commandeth even the winds and water, and they obey him.

00:55:27.818 --> 00:55:33.578
And they arrived at the country of the Gadarenes, which is over against Galilee, and when he went

00:55:33.578 --> 00:55:39.538
forth to land there met him out of the city a certain man which had devils long time, and

00:55:39.538 --> 00:55:46.198
clothes, neither abode in any house, but in the tombs. When he saw Jesus he cried out and

00:55:46.198 --> 00:55:52.158
fell down before him, and with a loud voice said, What have I to do with thee, Jesus,

00:55:52.418 --> 00:55:59.898
thou son of God most high? I beseech thee, torment me not. For he had commanded the unclean

00:55:59.898 --> 00:56:06.138
spirit to come out of the man. For often times it had caught him, and he was kept bound with

00:56:06.138 --> 00:56:12.178
chains and in fetters, and he break the bands, and was driven of the devil into the wilderness.

00:56:13.358 --> 00:56:20.638
And Jesus asked him, saying, What is thy name? And he said, Legion, because many devils were

00:56:20.638 --> 00:56:26.458
entered into him, and they besought him that he would not command them to go out into the deep.

00:56:27.438 --> 00:56:33.498
And there was there and heard of many swine feeding on the mountain, and they besought him

00:56:33.498 --> 00:56:39.858
he would suffer them to enter into them, and he suffered them. Then went the devils out of the

00:56:39.858 --> 00:56:46.198
man and entered into the swine, and the herd ran violently down a steep place into the lake,

00:56:46.298 --> 00:56:52.878
and were choked. When they that fed them saw what was done, they fled and went and told it in the

00:56:52.878 --> 00:56:59.818
city and in the country. Then they went out to see what was done, and came to Jesus, and found the

00:56:59.818 --> 00:57:06.978
man out of whom the devils were departed, sitting at the feet of Jesus, clothed, and in his right mind,

00:57:07.318 --> 00:57:14.998
and they were afraid. They also which saw it told them by what means he that was possessed of the

00:57:14.998 --> 00:57:20.538
devils was healed. Then the whole multitude of the country of the Gadarenes round about besought him

00:57:20.538 --> 00:57:25.938
to depart from them, for they were taken with great fear, and he went up into the ship and

00:57:25.938 --> 00:57:31.618
returned back again. Now the man out of whom the devils were departed besought him that he might be

00:57:31.618 --> 00:57:39.138
with him, but Jesus sent him away saying, return to thine own house and show how great things God

00:57:39.138 --> 00:57:45.038
hath done unto thee. And he went his way and published throughout the whole city how great

00:57:45.038 --> 00:57:52.098
things Jesus had done unto him. And it came to pass that when Jesus was returned the people

00:57:52.098 --> 00:57:59.158
gladly received him, for they were all waiting for him. And behold there came a man named Jairus,

00:57:59.378 --> 00:58:04.858
and he was a ruler of the synagogue, and he fell down at Jesus's feet, and besought him that he

00:58:04.858 --> 00:58:11.918
would come into his house, for he had one only daughter, about twelve years of age, and she lay

00:58:11.918 --> 00:58:18.578
a dying. But as he went the people thronged him, and a woman having an issue of blood twelve years,

00:58:18.578 --> 00:58:24.338
which had spent all her living upon physicians, neither could be healed of any, came behind him

00:58:24.338 --> 00:58:30.978
and touched the border of his garment, and immediately her issue of blood staunched. And

00:58:30.978 --> 00:58:38.238
Jesus said, Who touched me? When all denied, Peter and they that were with him said, Master,

00:58:38.698 --> 00:58:44.438
the multitude throng thee and press thee, and sayest thou who touched me? And Jesus said,

00:58:44.438 --> 00:58:51.618
Somebody hath touched me, for I perceive that virtue is gone out of me. And when the woman saw

00:58:51.618 --> 00:58:57.478
that she was not hit, she came trembling, and falling down before him, she declared unto him

00:58:57.478 --> 00:59:03.818
before all the people for what cause she had touched him, and how she was healed immediately.

00:59:04.538 --> 00:59:10.638
And he said unto her, Daughter, be of good comfort, thy faith hath made thee whole,

00:59:10.638 --> 00:59:17.358
go in peace. While he yet spake, there cometh one from the ruler of the synagogue's house,

00:59:17.418 --> 00:59:24.118
saying to him, Thy daughter is dead, trouble not the master. But when Jesus heard it, he answered

00:59:24.118 --> 00:59:31.738
him saying, Fear not, believe only, and she shall be made whole. And when he came into the house,

00:59:31.818 --> 00:59:40.618
he suffered no man to go in, save Peter and James and John, and the father and the mother of the

00:59:40.618 --> 00:59:47.838
people wept, and bewailed her. But he said, Weep not, she is not dead, but sleepeth. And they

00:59:47.838 --> 00:59:54.698
laughed him to scorn, knowing that she was dead. And he put them all out, and took her by the hand,

00:59:54.938 --> 01:00:04.058
and called, saying, Maid, arise. And her spirit came again, and she arose straightway, and he

01:00:04.058 --> 01:00:09.978
commanded to give her meat. And her parents were astonished, but he charged them that they should

01:00:09.978 --> 01:00:16.378
tell no man what was done.

01:00:50.672 --> 01:00:56.852
Then he called his twelve disciples together, and gave them power and authority over all

01:00:56.852 --> 01:01:02.452
devils, and to cure diseases. And he sent them to preach the kingdom of God, and to

01:01:02.452 --> 01:01:09.172
heal the sick. And he said unto them, Take nothing for your journey, neither staves nor

01:01:09.172 --> 01:01:15.152
scrip, neither bread, neither money, neither have two coats apiece, and whatsoever house

01:01:15.152 --> 01:01:22.992
ye enter into, there abide, and thence depart. And whosoever will not receive you, when ye

01:01:22.992 --> 01:01:28.592
go out of that city, shake off the very dust from your feet for a testimony against them.

01:01:29.472 --> 01:01:34.172
And they departed, and went through the towns, preaching the gospel, and healing everywhere.

01:01:35.272 --> 01:01:41.792
Now Herod the Tetrarch heard of all that was done by him, and he was perplexed, because

01:01:41.792 --> 01:01:47.672
that it was said of some that John was risen from the dead, and of some that Elias had

01:01:47.672 --> 01:01:55.172
and of others that one of the old prophets was risen again. And Herod said, John have

01:01:55.172 --> 01:02:02.572
I beheaded, but who is this of whom I hear such things? And he desired to see him. And

01:02:02.572 --> 01:02:07.612
the apostles, when they were returned, told him all that they had done, and he took them

01:02:07.612 --> 01:02:14.092
and went aside privately into a desert place belonging to the city called Bethsaida. And

01:02:14.092 --> 01:02:18.612
the people, when they knew it, followed him. And he received them, and spake unto them

01:02:18.612 --> 01:02:24.392
of the kingdom of God, and healed them that had need of healing. And when the day began

01:02:24.392 --> 01:02:30.292
to wear away, then came the twelve, and said unto him, Send the multitude away, that they

01:02:30.292 --> 01:02:36.352
may go into the towns, and country round about, and lodge, and get vigils, for we are here

01:02:36.352 --> 01:02:43.572
in a desert place. But he said unto them, Give ye them to eat. And they said, We have

01:02:43.572 --> 01:02:48.972
no more but five loaves and two fishes, except we should go and buy meat for all this people.

01:02:49.672 --> 01:02:55.532
For they were about five thousand men. And he said to his disciples, Make them sit down

01:02:55.532 --> 01:03:03.052
by fifties in a company. And they did so, and made them all sit down. Then he took the

01:03:03.052 --> 01:03:08.772
five loaves and the two fishes, and looking up to heaven he blessed them and break, and

01:03:08.772 --> 01:03:15.132
gave to the disciples to set before the multitude. And they did eat, and were all filled, and

01:03:15.132 --> 01:03:21.412
there was taken up of fragments that remained to them twelve baskets. And it came to pass,

01:03:21.432 --> 01:03:26.412
as he was alone praying, his disciples were with him, and he asked them, saying, Whom

01:03:26.412 --> 01:03:33.852
say the people that I am? They answering said, John the Baptist. But some say, Elias, and

01:03:33.852 --> 01:03:39.972
others say, that one of the old prophets is risen again. And he said unto them, But whom

01:03:39.972 --> 01:03:48.832
say ye that I am? Peter answering said, The Christ of God. And he straightly charged

01:03:48.832 --> 01:03:54.072
them and commanded them to tell no man that thing, saying, The son of man must suffer

01:03:54.072 --> 01:04:00.332
many things, and be rejected of the elders and chief priests and scribes, and be slain,

01:04:00.332 --> 01:04:07.412
and be raised the third day. And he said to them all, If any man will come after me, let

01:04:07.412 --> 01:04:13.652
him deny himself, and take up his cross daily, and follow me. For whosoever will save his

01:04:13.652 --> 01:04:19.112
life shall lose it. But whosoever will lose his life for my sake, the same shall save

01:04:19.112 --> 01:04:25.532
it. For what is a man advantaged if he gain the whole world, and lose himself, or be cast

01:04:25.532 --> 01:04:32.232
away? For whosoever shall be ashamed of me, and of my words, of him shall the son of man

01:04:32.232 --> 01:04:37.732
be ashamed, when he shall come in his own glory, and in his father's, and of the holy

01:04:37.732 --> 01:04:43.252
angels. But I tell you of a truth, there be some standing here, which shall not taste

01:04:43.252 --> 01:04:49.912
of death, till they see the kingdom of God. And it came to pass, about an eight days after

01:04:49.912 --> 01:04:55.032
these sayings, he took Peter and John and James, and went up into a mountain to pray.

01:04:55.712 --> 01:05:02.632
And as he prayed, the fashion of his countenance was altered, and his raiment was white and

01:05:02.632 --> 01:05:08.292
glistering. And behold, there talked with him two men, which were Moses and Elias, who

01:05:08.292 --> 01:05:14.892
appeared in glory, and spake of his decease, which he should accomplish at Jerusalem. But

01:05:14.892 --> 01:05:19.592
Peter and they that were with him were heavy with sleep, and when they were awake, they

01:05:19.592 --> 01:05:25.812
saw his glory, and the two men that stood with him. And it came to pass, as they departed

01:05:25.812 --> 01:05:31.412
from him, Peter said unto Jesus, Master, it is good for us to be here, and let us make

01:05:31.412 --> 01:05:37.312
three tabernacles, one for thee, and one for Moses, and one for Elias, not knowing what

01:05:37.312 --> 01:05:43.332
he said. While he thus spake, there came a cloud, and overshadowed them, and they feared

01:05:43.332 --> 01:05:48.452
as they entered into the cloud. And there came a voice out of the cloud saying, This

01:05:48.452 --> 01:05:55.592
is my beloved son, hear him. And when the voice was passed, Jesus was found alone, and

01:05:55.592 --> 01:06:01.212
they kept it close, and told no man in those days any of those things which they had seen.

01:06:02.112 --> 01:06:06.752
And it came to pass, that on the next day, when they were come down from the hill, much

01:06:06.752 --> 01:06:13.252
people met him. And behold, a man of the company cried out, saying, Master, I beseech thee,

01:06:13.552 --> 01:06:20.552
look upon my son, for he is mine only child. And lo, a spirit taketh him, and he suddenly

01:06:20.552 --> 01:06:26.552
crieth out, and it teareth him, that he foameth again, and bruising him, hardly departeth

01:06:26.552 --> 01:06:32.772
from him. And I besought thy disciples to cast him out, and they could not. And Jesus

01:06:32.772 --> 01:06:40.132
answering said, O faithless and perverse generation, how long shall I be with you, and suffer you?

01:06:40.452 --> 01:06:48.372
Bring thy son hither. And as he was yet a-coming, the devil threw him down, and tear him. And

01:06:48.372 --> 01:06:53.592
Jesus rebuked the unclean spirit, and healed the child, and delivered him again to his

01:06:53.592 --> 01:06:59.772
father. And they were all amazed at the mighty power of God. But while they wondered every

01:06:59.772 --> 01:07:06.192
one at all things which Jesus did, he said unto his disciples, Let these sayings sink

01:07:06.192 --> 01:07:12.552
down into your ears, for the Son of man shall be delivered into the hands of men. But they

01:07:12.552 --> 01:07:17.312
understood not this saying, and it was hid from them, that they perceived it not, and

01:07:17.312 --> 01:07:23.712
they feared to ask him of that saying. Then there arose a reasoning among them, which

01:07:23.712 --> 01:07:29.612
of them should be the greatest. And Jesus, perceiving the thought of their heart, took

01:07:29.612 --> 01:07:34.932
a child, and set him by him, and said unto them, Whosoever shall receive this child in

01:07:34.932 --> 01:07:41.612
thy name, receiveth me. And whosoever shall receive me, receiveth him that sent me. For

01:07:41.612 --> 01:07:48.792
he that is least among you all, the same shall be great. And John answered, and said, Master,

01:07:48.812 --> 01:07:54.792
we saw one casting out devils in thy name, and we forbade him, because he followeth not

01:07:54.792 --> 01:08:01.372
with us. And Jesus said unto him, Forbid him not, for he that is not against us, is for

01:08:01.372 --> 01:08:07.892
us. And it came to pass, when the time was come, that he should be received up, he steadfastly

01:08:07.892 --> 01:08:13.412
set his face to go to Jerusalem, and sent messengers before his face, and they went,

01:08:13.812 --> 01:08:19.792
and entered into a village of the Samaritans, to make ready for him. And they did not receive

01:08:19.792 --> 01:08:26.492
him, because his face was as though he would go to Jerusalem. And when his disciples, James

01:08:26.492 --> 01:08:31.492
and John saw this, they said, Lord, wilt thou that we command fire to come down from

01:08:31.492 --> 01:08:37.212
heaven and consume them, even as Elias did? But he turned, and rebuked them, and said,

01:08:37.852 --> 01:08:43.812
Ye know not what manner of spirit ye are of. For the Son of man is not come to destroy

01:08:43.812 --> 01:08:49.772
men's lives, but to save them. And they went to another village, and it came to pass, that,

01:08:50.052 --> 01:08:55.992
as they went in the way, a certain man said unto him, Lord, I will follow thee whithersoever

01:08:55.992 --> 01:09:03.392
thou goest. And Jesus said unto them, Foxes have holes, and birds of the air have nests,

01:09:03.812 --> 01:09:11.732
but the Son of man hath not where to lay his head. And he said unto another, Follow me.

01:09:12.012 --> 01:09:18.412
But he said, Lord, suffer me first to go and bury my father. Jesus said unto him, Let the

01:09:18.412 --> 01:09:24.672
dead bury their dead, but go thou and preach the kingdom of God. And another also said,

01:09:24.672 --> 01:09:30.072
Lord, I will follow thee, but let me first go bid them farewell, which are at home at

01:09:30.072 --> 01:09:36.732
my house. And Jesus said unto him, No man, having put his hand to the plow, and looking

01:09:36.732 --> 01:09:42.112
back, is fit for the kingdom of God

01:09:43.112 --> 01:09:47.772
After these things the Lord appointed other seventy also, and sent them two and two before

01:09:47.772 --> 01:09:54.512
his face into every city and place, whether he himself would come. Therefore said he unto

01:09:54.512 --> 01:10:00.972
them, The harvest truly is great, but the laborers are few. Pray ye therefore the Lord

01:10:00.972 --> 01:10:08.012
of the harvest that he would send forth laborers into his harvest. Go your ways. Behold I send

01:10:08.012 --> 01:10:14.452
you forth as lambs among wolves, carrying neither purse nor scrip nor shoes, and salute

01:10:14.452 --> 01:10:21.632
no man by the way. And into whatsoever house ye enter first say, Peace be to this house.

01:10:21.632 --> 01:10:28.312
And if the Son of Peace be there, your peace shall rest upon it. If not, it shall turn

01:10:28.312 --> 01:10:34.952
to you again. And in the same house remain eating and drinking such things as they give,

01:10:35.372 --> 01:10:41.452
for the laborer is worthy of his hire. Go not from house to house. And into whatsoever

01:10:41.452 --> 01:10:47.752
city ye enter, and they receive you, eat such things as are set before you. And heal the

01:10:47.752 --> 01:10:52.872
sick that are therein, and say unto them, The kingdom of God is come nigh unto you.

01:10:53.512 --> 01:10:59.512
But into whatsoever city ye enter, and they receive you not, go your ways out into the

01:10:59.512 --> 01:11:05.952
streets of the same, and say, Even the very dust of your city which cleaveth on us, we

01:11:05.952 --> 01:11:12.152
do wipe off against you. Notwithstanding be ye sure of this, that the kingdom of God is

01:11:12.152 --> 01:11:18.112
come nigh unto you. But I say unto you that it shall be more tolerable in that day for

01:11:18.112 --> 01:11:27.692
Sodom than for that city. Woe unto thee, Chorazin! Woe unto thee, Bethsaida! For if the mighty

01:11:27.692 --> 01:11:34.232
works had been done in Tyre and Sidon which have been done in you, they had a great while

01:11:34.232 --> 01:11:41.872
ago repented sitting in sackcloth and ashes. But it shall be more tolerable for Tyre and

01:11:41.872 --> 01:11:48.992
Sidon at the judgment than for you. And thou, Capernaum, which art exalted to heaven, shalt

01:11:48.992 --> 01:11:56.192
be thrust down to hell. He that heareth you heareth me, and he that despiseth you despiseth

01:11:56.712 --> 01:12:02.292
me, and he that despiseth me despiseth him that sent me.

01:12:03.072 --> 01:12:07.812
And the seven ye returned again with joy, saying, Lord, even the devils are subject

01:12:07.812 --> 01:12:14.272
unto us through thy name. And he said unto them, I beheld Satan as lightning fall from

01:12:14.272 --> 01:12:21.292
heaven. Behold, I give unto you power to tread on serpents and scorpions, and over all the

01:12:21.292 --> 01:12:28.052
power of the enemy, and nothing shall by any means hurt you. Notwithstanding in this rejoice

01:12:28.052 --> 01:12:33.892
not, that the spirits are subject unto you, but rather rejoice because your names are

01:12:33.892 --> 01:12:41.232
written in heaven. In that hour Jesus rejoiced in spirit and said, I thank thee, O Father,

01:12:41.432 --> 01:12:47.092
Lord of heaven and earth, that thou hast hid these things from the wise and prudent, and

01:12:47.092 --> 01:12:55.232
hast revealed them unto babes. Even so, Father, for so it seemed good in thy sight. All things

01:12:55.232 --> 01:13:01.672
are delivered to me of my Father, and no man knoweth who the Son is but the Father, and

01:13:01.672 --> 01:13:06.512
the Father is but the Son, and he to whom the Son will reveal him.

01:13:07.272 --> 01:13:12.992
And he turned him unto his disciples and said privately, Blessed are the eyes which see

01:13:12.992 --> 01:13:19.032
the things that ye see, for I tell you that many prophets and kings have desired to see

01:13:19.032 --> 01:13:25.212
those things which ye see, and have not seen them, and to hear those things which ye hear,

01:13:25.212 --> 01:13:32.652
and have not heard them. And behold a certain lawyer stood up and tempted him saying, Master,

01:13:32.772 --> 01:13:39.492
what shall I do to inherit eternal life? And he said unto him, What is written in the law?

01:13:40.292 --> 01:13:46.132
How readest thou? And he answering said, Thou shalt love the Lord thy God with all thy

01:13:46.132 --> 01:13:52.012
heart and with all thy soul and with all thy strength and with all thy mind and thy neighbor

01:13:52.012 --> 01:13:59.732
as thyself. And he said unto him, Thou hast answered right, this do, and thou shalt live.

01:14:00.192 --> 01:14:07.072
But he, willing to justify himself, said unto Jesus, And who is my neighbor? And Jesus answering

01:14:07.072 --> 01:14:13.372
said, A certain man went down from Jerusalem to Jericho and fell among thieves which stripped

01:14:13.372 --> 01:14:19.732
him of his raiment and wounded him and departed, leaving him half dead. And by chance there

01:14:19.732 --> 01:14:25.872
came down a certain priest that way, and when he saw him he passed by on the other side.

01:14:26.792 --> 01:14:33.292
And likewise a Levite, when he was at the place, came and looked on him and passed by

01:14:33.292 --> 01:14:40.072
on the other side. But a certain Samaritan, as he journeyed, came where he was and when

01:14:40.072 --> 01:14:46.612
he saw him he had compassion on him, and went to him and bound up his wounds pouring in

01:14:46.612 --> 01:14:52.632
oil and wine, and set him on his own beast, and brought him to an inn and took care of

01:14:52.632 --> 01:14:58.472
him. And on the morrow when he departed he took out two pence and gave them to the host

01:14:58.472 --> 01:15:05.092
and said unto him, Take care of him and whatsoever thou spendest more, when I come again I will

01:15:05.092 --> 01:15:12.352
repay thee. Which now of these three thinkest thou was neighbor unto him that fell among

01:15:12.352 --> 01:15:20.792
the thieves. And he said, He that showed mercy on him. Then said Jesus unto him, Go and do

01:15:20.792 --> 01:15:26.032
thou likewise. Now it came to pass, as they went, that he entered into a certain village

01:15:26.032 --> 01:15:31.512
and a certain woman named Martha received him into her house. And she had a sister called

01:15:31.512 --> 01:15:37.892
Mary, which also sat at Jesus' feet and heard his word. But Martha was cumbered about,

01:15:37.892 --> 01:15:43.952
much serving, and came to him and said, Lord, dost thou not care that my sister hath left

01:15:43.952 --> 01:15:49.752
me to serve alone? Bid her therefore that she help me. And Jesus answered and said unto

01:15:49.752 --> 01:15:55.612
her, Martha, Martha, thou art careful and troubled about many things, but one thing

01:15:55.612 --> 01:16:02.572
is needful, and Mary hath chosen that good part which shall not be taken away from her.

01:16:16.732 --> 01:16:18.132
Amen.

01:16:55.434 --> 01:17:02.614
And it came to pass, that as he was praying in a certain place, when he ceased, one of

01:17:02.614 --> 01:17:09.334
his disciples said unto him, Lord, teach us to pray, as John also taught his disciples.

01:17:10.494 --> 01:17:18.574
And he said unto them, When ye pray, say, Our Father which art in heaven, Hallowed be

01:17:18.574 --> 01:17:25.974
thy name, Thy kingdom come, thy will be done, as in heaven so in earth.

01:17:26.814 --> 01:17:35.034
Give us day by day our daily bread, and forgive us our sins, for we also forgive every one that

01:17:35.034 --> 01:17:41.754
is indebted to us, and lead us not into temptation, but deliver us from evil.

01:17:43.674 --> 01:17:49.954
And he said unto them, Which of you shall have a friend, and shall go unto him at midnight,

01:17:50.334 --> 01:17:56.854
And say unto him, Friend, lend me three loaves, for a friend of mine in his journey has come

01:17:56.854 --> 01:17:59.534
to me, and I have nothing to set before him.

01:18:00.534 --> 01:18:06.614
And he from within shall answer and say, Trouble me not, the door is now shut, and my children

01:18:06.614 --> 01:18:09.714
are with me in bed, I cannot rise and give thee.

01:18:10.694 --> 01:18:17.214
I say unto you, Though he will not rise and give him because he is his friend, yet because

01:18:17.214 --> 01:18:22.394
of his importunity he will rise and give him as many as he needeth.

01:18:23.234 --> 01:18:31.974
And I say unto you, Ask, and it shall be given you, seek, and ye shall find, knock, and it

01:18:31.974 --> 01:18:34.194
shall be opened unto you.

01:18:34.714 --> 01:18:41.194
For every one that asketh receiveth, and he that seeketh findeth, and to him that knocketh,

01:18:41.474 --> 01:18:42.554
it shall be opened.

01:18:44.294 --> 01:18:49.854
If a son shall ask bread of any of you that is a father, will he give him a stone?

01:18:50.654 --> 01:18:54.914
Or if he ask a fish, will he for a fish give him a serpent?

01:18:55.834 --> 01:18:59.834
Or if he shall ask an egg, will he offer him a scorpion?

01:19:00.794 --> 01:19:07.134
If ye then, being evil, know how to give good gifts unto your children, how much more shall

01:19:07.134 --> 01:19:11.374
your heavenly Father give the Holy Spirit to them that ask him?

01:19:13.734 --> 01:19:20.114
And he was casting out a devil, and it was dumb, and it came to pass when the devil was

01:19:20.114 --> 01:19:23.414
gone out, the dumb spake, and the people wondered.

01:19:24.354 --> 01:19:31.174
But some of them said, He casteth out devils through bales above the chief of the devils,

01:19:31.954 --> 01:19:35.514
and others tempting him sought of him a sign from heaven.

01:19:35.514 --> 01:19:43.114
But he, knowing their thoughts, said unto them, Every kingdom divided against itself

01:19:43.114 --> 01:19:48.034
is brought to desolation, and a house divided against a house falleth.

01:19:48.914 --> 01:19:54.114
If Satan also be divided against himself, how shall his kingdom stand?

01:19:55.154 --> 01:19:58.274
Because ye say that I cast out devils through bales above.

01:19:58.994 --> 01:20:04.274
And if I by bales above cast out devils, by whom do your sons cast them out?

01:20:05.014 --> 01:20:06.734
Therefore shall they be your judges.

01:20:08.054 --> 01:20:14.714
But if I with the finger of God cast out devils, no doubt the kingdom of God is come upon you.

01:20:15.874 --> 01:20:20.614
When a strong man armed keepeth his palace, his goods are in peace.

01:20:21.134 --> 01:20:27.194
But when a stronger than he shall come upon him, and overcome him, he taketh from him

01:20:27.194 --> 01:20:31.734
all his armor wherein he trusted, and divideth his spoils.

01:20:32.694 --> 01:20:38.994
He that is not with me is against me, and he that gathereth not with me scattereth.

01:20:40.674 --> 01:20:46.114
When the unclean spirit is gone out of a man, he walketh through dry places seeking rest,

01:20:46.474 --> 01:20:51.334
and finding none he saith, I will return unto my house whence I came out.

01:20:52.094 --> 01:20:55.774
And when he cometh, he findeth it swept and garnished.

01:20:55.774 --> 01:21:01.854
Then goeth he, and taketh to him seven other spirits more wicked than himself.

01:21:02.874 --> 01:21:09.294
And they enter in, and dwell there, and the last state of that man is worse than the first.

01:21:12.254 --> 01:21:18.514
And it came to pass, as he spake these things, a certain woman of the company lifted up her voice,

01:21:18.614 --> 01:21:24.394
and said unto him, Blessed is the womb that bare thee, and the paps which thou hast sucked.

01:21:25.514 --> 01:21:32.174
But he said, Yea, rather blessed are they that hear the word of God, and keep it.

01:21:34.514 --> 01:21:41.914
And when the people were gathered thick together, he began to say, This is an evil generation.

01:21:42.514 --> 01:21:48.794
They seek a sign, and there shall no sign be given it but the sign of Jonas the prophet.

01:21:49.434 --> 01:21:57.474
For as Jonas was a sign unto the Ninevites, so shall also the Son of Man be to this generation.

01:21:58.614 --> 01:22:03.414
The Queen of the South shall rise up in the judgment with the men of this generation,

01:22:03.794 --> 01:22:09.754
and condemn them. For she came from the utmost parts of the earth to hear the wisdom of Solomon,

01:22:10.214 --> 01:22:17.174
and behold a greater than Solomon is here. The men of Nineveh shall rise up in the judgment

01:22:17.174 --> 01:22:22.654
with this generation, and shall condemn it. For they repented at the preaching of Jonas,

01:22:23.074 --> 01:22:30.334
and behold a greater than Jonas is here. No man when he hath lighted a candle putteth it in a

01:22:30.334 --> 01:22:37.314
secret place, neither under a bushel, but on a candlestick, that they which come in may see the

01:22:37.314 --> 01:22:45.314
light. The light of the body is the eye. Therefore when thine eye is single, thy whole body also is

01:22:45.314 --> 01:22:53.054
full of light. But when thine eye is evil, thy body also is full of darkness. Take heed therefore

01:22:53.054 --> 01:23:00.274
that the light which is in thee be not darkness. If thy whole body therefore be full of light,

01:23:00.514 --> 01:23:06.434
having no part dark, the whole shall be full of light, as when the bright shining of a candle

01:23:09.714 --> 01:23:17.634
And as he spake, a certain Pharisee besought him to dine with him, and he went in, and sat down to

01:23:17.634 --> 01:23:24.994
meet. And when the Pharisees saw it, he marvelled that he had not first washed before dinner. And

01:23:24.994 --> 01:23:31.354
the Lord said unto him, Now do ye Pharisees make clean the outside of the cup and the platter,

01:23:31.354 --> 01:23:38.614
But your inward part is full of ravening and wickedness. Ye fools, did not he that made that

01:23:38.614 --> 01:23:45.414
which is without make that which is within also? But rather give alms of such things as ye have,

01:23:45.774 --> 01:23:51.954
and behold all things are clean unto you. But woe unto you Pharisees, for ye tithe the

01:23:51.954 --> 01:23:58.014
minth and rue and all manner of herbs, and pass over judgment and the love of God. These ought

01:23:58.014 --> 01:24:05.114
ye to have done, and not to leave the other undone. Woe unto you Pharisees, for ye love

01:24:05.114 --> 01:24:11.174
the uppermost seats in the synagogues and greetings in the markets. Woe unto you scribes

01:24:11.174 --> 01:24:18.214
and Pharisees, hypocrites, for ye are as graves which appear not, and the men that walk over them

01:24:18.214 --> 01:24:26.094
are not aware of them. Then answered one of the lawyers, and said unto him, Master, thus saying

01:24:26.094 --> 01:24:34.254
thou reproaches us also. And he said, Woe unto you also ye lawyers, for ye laid men with burdens,

01:24:34.394 --> 01:24:41.514
grievous to be born, and ye yourselves touch not the burdens with one of your fingers. Woe unto you,

01:24:41.614 --> 01:24:47.774
for ye build the sepulchres of the prophets, and your fathers kill them. Truly ye bear witness that

01:24:47.774 --> 01:24:53.694
ye allow the deeds of your fathers, for they indeed kill them, and ye build their sepulchres.

01:24:54.594 --> 01:25:01.434
Therefore also said the Wisdom of God, I will send them prophets and apostles, and some of them

01:25:01.434 --> 01:25:07.894
they shall slay and persecute. That the blood of all the prophets which was shed from the foundation

01:25:07.894 --> 01:25:14.434
of the world may be required of this generation. From the blood of Abel unto the blood of Zacharias,

01:25:14.874 --> 01:25:21.234
which perished between the altar and the temple, verily I say unto you, it shall be required of

01:25:21.234 --> 01:25:28.034
this generation. Woe unto you lawyers, for ye have taken away the key of knowledge. Ye entered

01:25:28.034 --> 01:25:36.274
not in yourselves, and them that were entering in ye hindered. And as he said these things unto them,

01:25:36.654 --> 01:25:42.174
the scribes and the Pharisees began to urge him vehemently, and to provoke him to speak of

01:25:42.174 --> 01:25:48.114
many things, laying wait for him, and seeking to catch something out of his mouth that they

01:25:48.114 --> 01:25:57.994
might accuse him. In the meantime, when there were gathered together an innumerable

01:25:57.994 --> 01:26:05.074
multitude of people, insomuch that they trod one upon another, he began to say unto his disciples,

01:26:05.214 --> 01:26:12.674
first of all, Beware ye of the leaven of the Pharisees, which is hypocrisy. For there is

01:26:12.674 --> 01:26:19.994
nothing covered that shall not be revealed, neither hid that shall not be known. Therefore

01:26:19.994 --> 01:26:26.614
whatsoever ye have spoken in darkness shall be heard in the light, and that which ye have spoken

01:26:26.614 --> 01:26:34.074
in the ear, in closets, shall be proclaimed upon the housetops. And I say unto you, my friends,

01:26:34.434 --> 01:26:41.134
be not afraid of them that kill the body, and after that have no more that they can do. But I

01:26:41.134 --> 01:26:47.934
will forewarn you whom ye shall fear. Fear him which after he hath killed hath power to cast

01:26:47.934 --> 01:26:55.774
you into hell. Yea, I say unto you, fear him. Are not five sparrows sold for two farthings,

01:26:56.474 --> 01:27:02.614
and not one of them is forgotten before God? But even the very hairs of your head are all numbered.

01:27:03.494 --> 01:27:10.594
Fear not, therefore, ye are of more value than many sparrows. Also I say unto you,

01:27:10.734 --> 01:27:17.634
Whosoever shall confess me before men, him shall the Son of Man also confess before the angels of

01:27:17.634 --> 01:27:24.934
God. But he that denieth me before men shall be denied before the angels of God. And whosoever

01:27:24.934 --> 01:27:31.514
shall speak a word against the Son of Man, it shall be forgiven him. But unto him that blasphemeth

01:27:31.514 --> 01:27:38.514
against the Holy Ghost, it shall not be forgiven. And when they bring you unto the synagogues,

01:27:38.754 --> 01:27:44.774
and unto magistrates and powers, take ye no thought how or what thing ye shall answer,

01:27:45.094 --> 01:27:51.474
or what ye shall say. For the Holy Ghost shall teach you in the same hour what ye ought to say.

01:27:53.074 --> 01:27:59.494
And one of the companies said unto him, Master, speak to my brother that he divide the inheritance

01:27:59.494 --> 01:28:08.994
with me. And he said unto him, Man, who made me a judge or divider over you? And he said unto them,

01:28:09.414 --> 01:28:15.714
Take heed, and beware of covetousness, for a man's life consisteth not in the abundance

01:28:15.714 --> 01:28:23.094
of the things which he possesseth. And he spake a parable unto them, saying, The ground of a certain

01:28:23.094 --> 01:28:29.994
rich man brought forth plentifully. And he thought within himself, saying, What shall I do,

01:28:30.174 --> 01:28:37.314
because I have no room where to bestow my fruits? And he said, This I will do, I will pull down my

01:28:37.314 --> 01:28:44.974
barns and build greater, and there will I bestow all my fruits and my goods. And I will say to my

01:28:44.974 --> 01:28:52.134
soul, Soul, thou hast much goods laid up for many years, take thine ease, eat, drink, and be merry.

01:28:53.094 --> 01:28:59.714
But God said unto him, Thou fool, this night thy soul shall be required of thee,

01:29:00.314 --> 01:29:04.094
then whose shall those things be which thou hast provided?

01:29:05.354 --> 01:29:11.074
So is he that layeth up treasure for himself, and is not rich toward God.

01:29:12.814 --> 01:29:19.534
And he said unto his disciples, Therefore I say unto you, Take no thought for your life,

01:29:19.534 --> 01:29:27.694
what ye shall eat, neither for the body, what ye shall put on. The life is more than meat,

01:29:28.074 --> 01:29:34.574
and the body is more than raiment. Consider the ravens, for they neither sow nor reap,

01:29:35.194 --> 01:29:41.654
which neither have storehouse nor barn, and God feedeth them. How much more are ye better

01:29:41.654 --> 01:29:48.474
than the fowls? And which of you, with taking thought, can add to his stature one cubit?

01:29:49.034 --> 01:29:55.034
If ye then be not able to do that thing which is least, why take ye thought for the rest?

01:29:56.214 --> 01:30:04.514
Consider the lilies, how they grow, they toil not, they spin not. And yet I say unto you,

01:30:04.834 --> 01:30:08.674
that Solomon in all his glory was not arrayed like one of these.

01:30:09.914 --> 01:30:16.954
If then God so clothe the grass, which is today in the field and tomorrow is cast into the oven,

01:30:17.594 --> 01:30:25.474
how much more will he clothe you, O ye of little faith? And seek not ye what ye shall eat or what

01:30:25.474 --> 01:30:32.434
ye shall drink, neither be ye of doubtful mind. For all these things do the nations of the world

01:30:32.434 --> 01:30:39.754
seek after, and your Father knoweth that ye have need of these things. But rather seek ye the kingdom

01:30:39.754 --> 01:30:48.514
of God, and all these things shall be added unto you. Fear not, little flock, for it is your

01:30:48.514 --> 01:30:55.954
Father's good pleasure to give you the kingdom. Sell that ye have, and give alms, provide yourselves

01:30:55.954 --> 01:31:02.914
bags which wax not old, a treasure in the heavens that faileth not, where no thief approacheth,

01:31:02.914 --> 01:31:09.714
neither moth corrupteth. For where your treasure is, there will your heart be also.

01:31:11.534 --> 01:31:18.074
Let your loins be girded about, and your lights burning. And ye yourselves like unto men that

01:31:18.074 --> 01:31:23.854
wait for their Lord, when he will return from the wedding, that when he cometh and knocketh,

01:31:24.074 --> 01:31:30.554
they may open unto him immediately. Blessed are those servants whom the Lord, when he cometh,

01:31:30.554 --> 01:31:37.714
shall find watching. Verily I say unto you that he shall gird himself and make them to sit down

01:31:37.714 --> 01:31:44.154
to meet, and will come forth and serve them. And if he shall come in the second watch,

01:31:44.454 --> 01:31:49.454
or come in the third watch, and find them so, blessed are those servants.

01:31:50.854 --> 01:31:56.554
And this know, that if the goodman of the house had known what hour the thief would come,

01:31:56.554 --> 01:32:01.014
he would have watched, and not have suffered his house to be broken through.

01:32:02.234 --> 01:32:08.614
Be therefore ready also, for the Son of Man cometh at an hour, when ye think not.

01:32:10.134 --> 01:32:17.374
Then Peter said unto him, Lord, speakest thou this parable unto us, or even to all?

01:32:18.274 --> 01:32:24.794
And the Lord said, Who then is that faithful and wise steward, whom his Lord shall make ruler over

01:32:24.794 --> 01:32:31.354
his household, to give them their portion of meat in due season? Blessed is that servant whom his

01:32:31.354 --> 01:32:38.594
Lord, when he cometh, shall find so doing. Of a truth I say unto you, that he will make him ruler

01:32:38.594 --> 01:32:46.494
over all that he hath. But, and if that servant say in his heart, My Lord delayeth his coming,

01:32:46.914 --> 01:32:52.254
and shall begin to beat the men's servants and maidens, and to eat and to drink and to be drunken,

01:32:52.254 --> 01:32:58.594
the Lord of that servant will come in a day when he looketh not for him, and at an hour when he is

01:32:58.594 --> 01:33:03.994
not aware, and will cut him in sunder, and will appoint him his portion with the unbelievers.

01:33:05.314 --> 01:33:11.394
And that servant which knew his Lord's will, and prepared not himself, neither did according to his

01:33:11.394 --> 01:33:18.654
will, shall be beaten with many stripes. But he that knew not, and did not commit things worthy

01:33:18.654 --> 01:33:27.054
of stripes, shall be beaten with few stripes. For unto whomsoever much is given, of him shall

01:33:27.054 --> 01:33:33.774
be much required. And to whom men have committed much, of him they will ask the more.

01:33:35.334 --> 01:33:41.214
I am come to send fire on the earth, and what will I if it be already kindled?

01:33:41.974 --> 01:33:48.314
But I have a baptism to be baptized with, and how am I straightened till it be accomplished?

01:33:49.214 --> 01:33:54.694
Suppose ye that I am come to give peace on earth, I tell you nay, but rather division.

01:33:55.754 --> 01:34:01.714
For from henceforth there shall be five in one house, divided three against two, and two against

01:34:01.714 --> 01:34:07.614
three. The father shall be divided against the son, and the son against the father, the mother

01:34:07.614 --> 01:34:12.814
against the daughter, and the daughter against the mother, the mother-in-law against her daughter-in-law,

01:34:12.814 --> 01:34:18.034
and the daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law. And he said also to the people,

01:34:18.574 --> 01:34:25.994
When ye see a cloud rise out of the west, straightway ye say, There cometh a shower, and so it is.

01:34:26.614 --> 01:34:33.774
And when ye see the south wind blow, ye say, There will be heat, and it cometh to pass. Ye

01:34:33.774 --> 01:34:39.974
hypocrites, ye can discern the face of the sky and of the earth, but how is it that ye do not

01:34:39.974 --> 01:34:46.454
discern this time? Yea, and why even of yourselves judge ye not what is right?

01:34:48.134 --> 01:34:53.274
When thou goest with thine adversary to the magistrate, as thou art in the way,

01:34:53.474 --> 01:34:58.694
give diligence that thou mayest be delivered from him, lest he hail thee to the judge,

01:34:59.094 --> 01:35:03.574
and the judge deliver thee to the officer, and the officer cast thee into prison.

01:35:03.574 --> 01:35:10.884
I tell thee, thou shalt not depart thence, till thou hast paid the very last might.

01:35:21.714 --> 01:35:27.574
READING BY FATHER ZILEY OF DETROIT, OCTOBER 2008

01:36:13.904 --> 01:36:19.364
There were present at that season some that told him of the Galileans whose blood Pilate

01:36:19.364 --> 01:36:25.004
had mingled with their sacrifices. And Jesus, answering, said unto them,

01:36:25.584 --> 01:36:30.864
Suppose ye that these Galileans were sinners above all the Galileans, because they suffered

01:36:30.864 --> 01:36:39.264
such things? I tell you nay. But except ye repent, ye shall all likewise perish. O those

01:36:39.264 --> 01:36:46.704
the tower in Siloam fell, and slew them, think ye that they were sinners above all men that

01:36:46.704 --> 01:36:53.664
dwelt in Jerusalem? I tell you nay. But except ye repent, ye shall all likewise perish.

01:36:55.484 --> 01:37:02.244
He spake also this parable. A certain man had a fig-tree planted in his vineyard, and

01:37:02.244 --> 01:37:08.124
he came and sought fruit thereon, and found none. Then said he unto the dresser of his

01:37:08.124 --> 01:37:13.604
vineyard, Behold, these three years I come seeking fruit on this fig-tree, and find none.

01:37:14.384 --> 01:37:20.404
Cut it down, why cumbereth it the ground? And he answering, said unto him,

01:37:20.844 --> 01:37:27.104
Lord, let it alone this year also, till I shall dig about it and dung it, and if it

01:37:27.104 --> 01:37:32.344
bear fruit well. And if not, then after that thou shalt cut it down.

01:37:33.024 --> 01:37:36.524
And he was teaching in one of the synagogues on the Sabbath.

01:37:38.104 --> 01:37:44.184
And behold, there was a woman which had a spirit of infirmity eighteen years, and was

01:37:44.184 --> 01:37:50.964
bowed together, and could in no wise lift up herself. And when Jesus saw her, he called

01:37:50.964 --> 01:37:57.804
her to him, and said unto her, Woman, thou art loosed from thine infirmity. And he laid

01:37:57.804 --> 01:38:03.104
his hands on her, and immediately she was made straight and glorified God.

01:38:04.184 --> 01:38:08.984
And the ruler of the synagogue answered with indignation, because that Jesus had healed

01:38:08.984 --> 01:38:15.024
on the Sabbath day, and said unto the people, There are six days in which men ought to work,

01:38:15.164 --> 01:38:18.744
in them therefore come and be healed, and not on the Sabbath day.

01:38:19.704 --> 01:38:27.024
The Lord then answered him, and said, Thou hypocrite, doth not each one of you on the

01:38:27.024 --> 01:38:33.344
Sabbath loose his ox or his ass from the stall, and lead him away to watering? And ought not

01:38:33.344 --> 01:38:38.204
this woman, being a daughter of Abraham, whom Satan hath bound low these eighteen years,

01:38:38.584 --> 01:38:44.664
be loosed from this bond on the Sabbath day? And when he had said these things, all his

01:38:44.664 --> 01:38:49.944
adversaries were ashamed, and all the people rejoiced for all the glorious things that

01:38:49.944 --> 01:38:51.204
were done by him.

01:38:52.864 --> 01:38:59.764
Then said he, Unto what is the kingdom of God like, and whereunto shall I resemble it?

01:39:00.684 --> 01:39:06.404
It is like a grain of mustard seed, which a man took and cast into his garden, and it

01:39:06.404 --> 01:39:11.924
grew and waxed a great tree, and the fowls of the air lodged in the branches of it.

01:39:13.044 --> 01:39:20.264
And again he said, Whereunto shall I liken the kingdom of God? It is like leaven, which

01:39:20.264 --> 01:39:25.484
a woman took and hid in three measures of meal till the whole was leavened.

01:39:26.344 --> 01:39:30.704
And he went through the cities and villages, teaching and journeying toward Jerusalem.

01:39:32.004 --> 01:39:40.524
Then said one unto him, Lord, are there few that be saved? And he said unto them, Strive

01:39:40.524 --> 01:39:46.784
to enter in at the straight gate, for many I say unto you will seek to enter in and shall

01:39:46.784 --> 01:39:53.984
not be able. When once the master of the house is risen up, and hath shut to the door, and

01:39:53.984 --> 01:39:59.824
ye begin to stand without and knock at the door, saying, Lord, Lord, open unto us, and

01:39:59.824 --> 01:40:06.444
he shall answer and say unto you, I know you not whence ye are. Then shall ye begin to

01:40:06.444 --> 01:40:12.704
say, We have eaten and drunk in thy presence, and thou hast taught in our streets. But he

01:40:12.704 --> 01:40:19.944
shall say, I tell you, I know you not whence ye are. Depart from me, all ye workers of

01:40:19.944 --> 01:40:26.984
iniquity. There shall be weeping and gnashing of teeth, when ye shall see Abraham and Isaac

01:40:26.984 --> 01:40:33.524
and Jacob and all the prophets in the kingdom of God, and you yourselves thrust out. And

01:40:33.524 --> 01:40:38.144
they shall come from the east and from the west, and from the north and from the south,

01:40:38.144 --> 01:40:45.044
and shall sit down in the kingdom of God. And behold there are last which shall be first,

01:40:45.424 --> 01:40:52.164
and there are first which shall be last. The same day there came certain of the Pharisees

01:40:52.164 --> 01:40:59.624
saying unto him, Get thee out and depart hence, for Herod will kill thee. And he said unto

01:40:59.624 --> 01:41:08.124
them, Go ye and tell that fox, behold, I cast out devils, and I do cures to-day and to-morrow

01:41:08.144 --> 01:41:15.644
and the third day I shall be perfected. Nevertheless I must walk to-day and to-morrow and the day

01:41:15.644 --> 01:41:23.184
following, for it cannot be that a prophet perish out of Jerusalem. O Jerusalem, Jerusalem,

01:41:23.684 --> 01:41:29.744
which killest the prophets and stonest them that are sent unto thee, how often would I

01:41:29.744 --> 01:41:34.244
have gathered thy children together, as a hen doth gather her brood under her wings,

01:41:34.244 --> 01:41:42.964
and ye would not. Behold your house is left unto you desolate, and verily I say unto you,

01:41:43.504 --> 01:41:50.084
ye shall not see me until the time come when ye shall say, Blessed is he that cometh in

01:41:50.084 --> 01:41:51.204
the name of the Lord.

01:41:53.184 --> 01:41:58.764
And it came to pass, as he went into the house of one of the chief Pharisees to eat bread

01:41:58.764 --> 01:42:04.704
on the Sabbath-day, that they watched him. And behold, there was a certain man before

01:42:04.704 --> 01:42:11.204
him which had the dropsy. And Jesus, answering, spake unto the lawyers and Pharisees, saying,

01:42:11.984 --> 01:42:18.604
Is it lawful to heal on the Sabbath-day? And they held their peace. And he took him and

01:42:18.604 --> 01:42:25.504
healed him, and let him go. And answered them, saying, Which of you shall have an ass or

01:42:25.504 --> 01:42:32.564
an ox fallen into a pit, and will not straightway pull him out on the Sabbath-day? And they

01:42:32.564 --> 01:42:38.124
could not answer him again to these things. And he put forth a parable to those which

01:42:38.124 --> 01:42:43.684
were bidden, when he marked how they chose out the chief rooms, saying unto them, When

01:42:43.684 --> 01:42:55.484
thou art bidden of any man to a wedding, sit not down in the highest room, lest a more

01:42:55.484 --> 01:43:03.364
to thee, give this man place, and thou begin with shame to take the lowest room. But when

01:43:03.364 --> 01:43:09.304
thou art bidden, go and sit down in the lowest room, that when he that bade thee cometh,

01:43:09.724 --> 01:43:16.264
he may say unto thee, Friend, go up higher. Then shalt thou have worship in the presence

01:43:16.264 --> 01:43:25.464
of them that sit at meet with thee. For whoever exalteth himself shall be abased, and he that

01:43:25.464 --> 01:43:26.504
shall be exalted.

01:43:28.524 --> 01:43:34.824
Then said he also unto him that bade him, When thou makest a dinner or a supper, call

01:43:34.824 --> 01:43:40.884
not thy friends nor thy brethren, neither thy kinsmen nor thy rich neighbours, lest

01:43:40.884 --> 01:43:46.524
they also bid thee again, and a recompense be made thee. But when thou makest a feast,

01:43:46.684 --> 01:43:53.444
call the poor, the maimed, the lame, the blind, and thou shalt be blessed, for they cannot

01:43:53.824 --> 01:43:58.904
recompense thee, for thou shalt be recompensed at the resurrection of the just.

01:44:00.424 --> 01:44:05.984
And when one of them that sat at meet with him heard these things, he said unto him,

01:44:06.304 --> 01:44:14.064
Blessed is he that shall eat bread in the kingdom of God. Then he said unto him, A certain

01:44:14.064 --> 01:44:20.404
man made a great supper and bade many, and sent his servants at supper time to say to

01:44:20.404 --> 01:44:24.544
them that were bidden, Come, for all things are now ready.

01:44:25.824 --> 01:44:32.504
And they all with one consent began to make excuse. The first said unto him, I have bought

01:44:32.504 --> 01:44:39.304
a piece of ground, and I must needs go and see it. I pray thee have me excused. And another

01:44:39.304 --> 01:44:46.704
said, I have bought five yoke of oxen, and I go to prove them. I pray thee have me excused.

01:44:46.704 --> 01:44:51.364
And another said, I have married a wife, and therefore I cannot come.

01:44:52.844 --> 01:44:58.204
So that servant came, and showed his lord these things. Then the master of the house

01:44:58.204 --> 01:45:04.524
being angry, said to his servant, Go out quickly into the streets and lanes of the city, and

01:45:04.524 --> 01:45:08.464
bring in hither the poor, and the maimed, and the halt, and the blind.

01:45:09.564 --> 01:45:14.824
And the servant said, Lord, it is done as thou hast commanded, and yet there is room.

01:45:15.544 --> 01:45:21.824
And the lord said unto the servant, Go out into the highways and hedges, and compel

01:45:21.824 --> 01:45:28.904
them to come in, that my house may be filled. For I say unto you, that none of those men

01:45:28.904 --> 01:45:36.644
which were bidden shall taste of my supper. And there went great multitudes with him,

01:45:36.884 --> 01:45:43.324
and he turned and said unto them, If any man come to me, and hate not his father and mother,

01:45:43.324 --> 01:45:51.344
and wife and children, and brethren and sisters, yea, and his own life also, he cannot be my

01:45:51.344 --> 01:45:59.044
disciple. And whosoever doth not bear his cross, and come after me, cannot be my disciple.

01:45:59.944 --> 01:46:06.184
For which of you intending to build a tower, sitteth not down first, and counteth the cost

01:46:06.184 --> 01:46:12.164
whether he have sufficient to finish it? Lest haply, after he hath laid the foundation,

01:46:12.164 --> 01:46:19.024
and is not able to finish it, all that behold it begin to mock him, saying, This man began

01:46:19.024 --> 01:46:25.564
to build, and was not able to finish. Or what king, going to make war against another king,

01:46:25.884 --> 01:46:32.084
sitteth not down first, and consulteth whether he be able with ten thousand to meet him that

01:46:32.084 --> 01:46:38.524
cometh against him with twenty thousand? Or else, while the other is yet a great way off,

01:46:38.884 --> 01:46:46.884
he sendeth an embassage, and desireth conditions of peace. So likewise, whosoever he be of

01:46:46.884 --> 01:46:55.124
you, that forsaketh not all he hath, he cannot be my disciple. Salt is good, but if the salt

01:46:55.124 --> 01:47:02.264
have lost his savor, wherewith shall it be seasoned? It is neither fit for the land,

01:47:02.264 --> 01:47:09.744
nor yet for the dung-hill, but men cast it out. He that hath ears to hear, let him hear.

01:48:08.125 --> 01:48:12.705
This is Father Zeile of Detroit, December 2008.

01:48:20.745 --> 01:48:24.765
Then drew near unto him all the publicans and sinners for to hear him.

01:48:25.325 --> 01:48:30.105
And the Pharisees and scribes murmured, saying, This man receiveth sinners,

01:48:30.365 --> 01:48:34.805
and eateth with them. And he spake this parable unto them, saying,

01:48:36.005 --> 01:48:40.165
What man of you, having an hundred sheep, if he lose one of them,

01:48:40.165 --> 01:48:45.545
doth not leave the ninety and nine in the wilderness, and go after that which is lost,

01:48:45.745 --> 01:48:51.645
until he find it? And when he hath found it, he layeth it on his shoulders, rejoicing.

01:48:52.565 --> 01:48:56.085
And when he cometh home, he calleth together his friends and neighbors,

01:48:56.245 --> 01:49:01.445
saying unto them, Rejoice with me, for I have found my sheep which was lost.

01:49:02.205 --> 01:49:08.385
I say unto you, that likewise joy shall be in heaven over one sinner that repenteth,

01:49:08.385 --> 01:49:13.205
more than over ninety and nine just persons which need no repentance.

01:49:15.305 --> 01:49:20.425
Either what woman, having ten pieces of silver, if she lose one piece,

01:49:20.845 --> 01:49:26.325
doth not light a candle, and sweep the house, and seek diligently till she find it.

01:49:26.565 --> 01:49:30.525
And when she hath found it, she calleth her friends and her neighbors together,

01:49:30.665 --> 01:49:35.125
saying, Rejoice with me, for I have found the piece which I had lost.

01:49:36.405 --> 01:49:42.945
Likewise I say unto you, there is joy in the presence of the angels of God over one sinner

01:49:42.945 --> 01:49:52.265
that repenteth. And he said, A certain man had two sons, and the younger of them said to his father,

01:49:53.085 --> 01:50:00.965
Father, give me the portion of goods that falleth to me. And he divided unto him his living.

01:50:02.445 --> 01:50:09.145
And not many days after the younger son gathered all together, and took his journey into a far

01:50:09.145 --> 01:50:16.205
country, and there wasted his substance with riotous living. And when he had spent all,

01:50:16.925 --> 01:50:23.685
there arose a mighty famine in that land, and he began to be in want. And he went and joined

01:50:23.685 --> 01:50:30.945
himself to a citizen of that country, and he sent him into his fields to feed swine. And he would

01:50:30.945 --> 01:50:37.165
have filled his belly with the husks that the swine did eat, and no man gave unto him.

01:50:38.585 --> 01:50:44.905
And when he came to himself, he said, How many hired servants of my fathers have

01:50:44.905 --> 01:50:52.065
bred enough and to spare, and I perish with hunger. I will arise and go to my father,

01:50:52.525 --> 01:50:58.465
and will say unto him, Father, I have sinned against heaven and before thee,

01:50:58.465 --> 01:51:04.965
and am no more worthy to be called thy son. Make me as one of thy hired servants.

01:51:06.025 --> 01:51:11.825
And he arose and came to his father. But when he was yet a great way off,

01:51:12.245 --> 01:51:18.105
his father saw him, and had compassion, and ran, and fell on his neck, and kissed him.

01:51:18.825 --> 01:51:25.505
And the son said unto him, Father, I have sinned against heaven, and in thy sight,

01:51:25.505 --> 01:51:32.045
and am no more worthy to be called thy son. But the father said to his servants,

01:51:33.005 --> 01:51:39.365
Bring forth the best robe, and put it on him, and put a ring on his hand, and shoes on his feet,

01:51:40.005 --> 01:51:46.685
and bring hither the fatted calf, and kill it, and let us eat, and be merry. For this my son was dead,

01:51:46.845 --> 01:51:53.185
and is alive again. He was lost, and is found. And they began to be merry.

01:51:53.885 --> 01:52:00.145
Now his elder brother was in the field, and as he came and drew nigh to the house,

01:52:00.705 --> 01:52:06.885
he heard music and dancing. And he called one of the servants, and asked what these things meant.

01:52:07.905 --> 01:52:13.705
And he said unto him, Thy brother is come, and thy father hath killed the fatted calf,

01:52:14.165 --> 01:52:22.465
because he hath received him safe and sound. And he was angry, and would not go in. Therefore

01:52:22.465 --> 01:52:29.125
came his father out, and entreated him. And he answering said to his father, Lo,

01:52:29.305 --> 01:52:35.085
these many years do I serve thee, neither transgressed I at any time thy commandment,

01:52:35.385 --> 01:52:42.305
and yet thou never gavest me a kid, that I might make merry with my friends. But as soon as this

01:52:42.305 --> 01:52:47.885
thy son was come, which hath devoured thy living with harlots, thou hast killed for him the fatted

01:52:47.885 --> 01:52:58.305
calf. And he said unto him, Son, thou art ever with me, and all that I have is thine. It was

01:52:58.305 --> 01:53:04.765
meet that we should make merry and be glad. For this thy brother was dead, and is alive again,

01:53:05.225 --> 01:53:11.225
and was lost, and is found

01:53:11.225 --> 01:53:18.845
And he said also unto his disciples, There was a certain rich man, which had a steward. And the

01:53:18.845 --> 01:53:24.745
same was accused unto him, that he had wasted his goods. And he called him, and said unto him,

01:53:25.405 --> 01:53:31.265
How is it that I hear this of thee? Give an account of thy stewardship, or thou mayest be

01:53:31.265 --> 01:53:38.105
no longer steward. Then the steward said within himself, What shall I do? For my Lord taketh

01:53:38.105 --> 01:53:45.725
away from me the stewardship. I cannot dig, to beg I am ashamed. I am resolved what to do,

01:53:45.985 --> 01:53:52.085
that when I am put out of the stewardship, they may receive me into their houses. So he called

01:53:52.085 --> 01:53:58.225
every one of his Lord's debtors unto him, and said unto the first, How much owest thou unto my

01:53:58.225 --> 01:54:06.225
Lord? And he said, On hundred measures of oil. And he said unto him, Take thy bill, and sit down

01:54:06.225 --> 01:54:13.645
quickly, and write fifty. Then said he to another, And how much owest thou? And he said,

01:54:13.965 --> 01:54:19.945
And hundred measures of wheat. And he said unto him, Take thy bill, and write four score.

01:54:21.305 --> 01:54:27.245
And the Lord commended the unjust steward, because he had done wisely, for the children

01:54:27.245 --> 01:54:33.565
of this world are in their generation wiser than the children of light. And I say unto you,

01:54:33.565 --> 01:54:39.165
Make to yourselves friends of the mammon of unrighteousness, that when ye fail,

01:54:39.665 --> 01:54:46.565
they may receive you into everlasting habitations. He that is faithful in that which is least,

01:54:46.985 --> 01:54:56.185
is faithful also in much. And he that is unjust in the least, is unjust also in much. If therefore

01:54:56.185 --> 01:55:02.425
ye have not been faithful in the unrighteous mammon, who will commit to your trust the true

01:55:02.425 --> 01:55:08.725
riches? And if ye have not been faithful in that which is another man's, who shall give you that

01:55:08.725 --> 01:55:15.645
which is your own? No servant can serve two masters, for either he will hate the one and

01:55:15.645 --> 01:55:22.565
love the other, or else he will hold to the one and despise the other. Ye cannot serve God and

01:55:22.565 --> 01:55:30.185
mammon. And the Pharisees also who were covetous heard all these things, and they derided him.

01:55:30.185 --> 01:55:37.645
And he said unto them, Ye are they which justify yourselves before men, but God knoweth your

01:55:37.645 --> 01:55:43.745
hearts. For that which is highly esteemed among men, is abomination in the sight of God.

01:55:44.625 --> 01:55:51.285
The law and the prophets were until John. Since that time the kingdom of God is preached,

01:55:51.545 --> 01:55:57.065
and every man presseth into it. And it is easier for heaven and earth to pass,

01:55:57.065 --> 01:56:03.705
than one tittle of the law to fail. Whosoever putteth away his wife, and marryeth another,

01:56:04.145 --> 01:56:08.625
committeth adultery. And whosoever marryeth her that is put away from her husband,

01:56:08.925 --> 01:56:15.485
committeth adultery. There was a certain rich man, which was clothed in purple and fine linen,

01:56:15.765 --> 01:56:22.225
and fared sumptuously every day. And there was a certain beggar named Lazarus, which was laid at

01:56:22.225 --> 01:56:28.405
his gate full of sores, and desiring to be fed with the crumbs which fell from the rich man's

01:56:28.405 --> 01:56:36.465
table. Moreover the dogs came, and licked his sores. And it came to pass, that the beggar died,

01:56:36.645 --> 01:56:43.685
and was carried by the angels into Abraham's bosom. The rich man also died, and was buried,

01:56:44.165 --> 01:56:51.305
and in hell he lifted up his eyes, being in torment, and seeth Abraham afar off and Lazarus

01:56:51.305 --> 01:56:58.765
in his bosom. And he cried, and said, Father Abraham, have mercy on me, and send Lazarus that he may

01:56:58.765 --> 01:57:04.425
dip the tip of his finger in water, and cool my tongue, for I am tormented in this flame.

01:57:05.985 --> 01:57:12.725
But Abraham said, Son, remember that thou in thy lifetime receivest thy good things,

01:57:13.025 --> 01:57:19.065
and likewise Lazarus' evil things. But now he is comforted, and thou are tormented.

01:57:19.925 --> 01:57:28.025
And beside all this, between us and you there is a great gulf fixed, so that they which would pass

01:57:28.025 --> 01:57:35.705
from hence to you cannot, neither can they pass to us that would come from thence. Then he said,

01:57:35.865 --> 01:57:41.925
I pray thee therefore, Father, that thou wouldest send him to my father's house, for I have five

01:57:41.925 --> 01:57:47.625
brethren, that he may testify unto them, lest they also come into this place of torment.

01:57:48.705 --> 01:57:56.265
Abraham saith unto him, They have Moses and the prophets, let them hear them. And he said,

01:57:56.525 --> 01:58:02.005
Nay, Father Abraham, but if one went unto them from the dead, they will repent.

01:58:03.105 --> 01:58:08.325
And he said unto him, If they hear not Moses and the prophets,

01:58:09.025 --> 01:58:12.985
neither will they be persuaded, though one rose from the dead.

01:59:06.290 --> 01:59:06.810
XVII.

01:59:07.590 --> 01:59:08.990
Then said he unto the disciples,

01:59:09.650 --> 01:59:16.550
It is impossible, but that offenses will come, But woe unto him through whom they come.

01:59:17.650 --> 01:59:23.730
It were better for him that a millstone were hanged about his neck, and he cast into the sea,

01:59:24.510 --> 01:59:27.070
Than that he should offend one of these little ones.

01:59:28.790 --> 01:59:36.050
Take heed to yourselves. If thy brother trespass against thee, rebuke him, and if he repent,

01:59:36.050 --> 01:59:43.330
forgive him. And if he trespass against thee seven times in a day, and seven times in a day,

01:59:43.450 --> 01:59:48.710
turn again to thee, saying, I repent, thou shalt forgive him.

01:59:49.990 --> 01:59:54.210
And the apostle said unto the Lord, Increase our faith.

01:59:55.010 --> 02:00:02.570
And the Lord said, If ye had faith as a grain of mustard seed, ye might say unto this sycamine

02:00:03.350 --> 02:00:09.650
Be thou plucked up by the root, and be thou planted in the sea, and it should obey you.

02:00:11.210 --> 02:00:17.070
But which of you, having a servant plowing or feeding cattle, will say unto him by and by,

02:00:17.150 --> 02:00:20.690
When he has come from the field, Go and sit down to meet?

02:00:22.190 --> 02:00:28.170
And will not rather say unto him, Make ready wherewith I may sup, and gird thyself,

02:00:28.170 --> 02:00:33.690
And serve me till I have eaten and drunken, and afterward thou shalt eat and drink?

02:00:34.690 --> 02:00:38.490
Dost he thank that servant because he did the things that were commanded him?

02:00:38.890 --> 02:00:45.970
I tro not. So likewise ye, when ye shall have done all those things which are commanded you,

02:00:46.510 --> 02:00:52.830
Say, We are unprofitable servants. We have done that which was our duty to do.

02:00:54.850 --> 02:01:01.210
And it came to pass, as he went to Jerusalem, that he passed through the midst of Samaria and

02:01:01.210 --> 02:01:07.610
Galilee. And as he entered into a certain village, there met him ten men that were lepers,

02:01:08.010 --> 02:01:15.510
which stood afar off. And they lifted up their voices, and said, Jesus, Master, have mercy on us.

02:01:16.430 --> 02:01:22.950
And when he saw them, he said unto them, Go, show yourselves unto the priests.

02:01:24.110 --> 02:01:30.990
And it came to pass that, as they went, they were cleansed. And one of them, when he saw that he

02:01:30.990 --> 02:01:38.710
was healed, turned back, and with a loud voice glorified God, and fell down on his face at his

02:01:38.710 --> 02:01:48.310
feet, giving him thanks. And he was a Samaritan. And Jesus, answering, said, Were there not ten

02:01:48.310 --> 02:01:56.430
cleansed? But where are the nine? There are not found that return to give glory to God save this

02:01:56.430 --> 02:02:04.510
stranger. And he said unto him, Arise, go thy way, thy faith hath made thee whole.

02:02:07.030 --> 02:02:13.490
And when he was demanded of the Pharisees, when the kingdom of God should come, he answered them

02:02:13.490 --> 02:02:20.990
and said, The kingdom of God cometh not with observation. Neither shall they say, Lo, here,

02:02:21.390 --> 02:02:30.030
or lo, there. For behold, the kingdom of God is within you. And he said unto the disciples,

02:02:30.670 --> 02:02:36.210
The days will come when ye shall desire to see one of the days of the Son of man,

02:02:36.250 --> 02:02:45.190
and ye shall not see it. And they shall say to you, See here, or see there. Go not after them,

02:02:45.350 --> 02:02:52.410
nor follow them. For as the lightning that lighteneth out of the one part under heaven,

02:02:52.890 --> 02:02:58.810
shineth unto the other part under heaven, so shall also the Son of man be in his day.

02:02:59.370 --> 02:03:04.390
But first must he suffer many things, and be rejected of this generation.

02:03:05.810 --> 02:03:12.470
And as it was in the days of Noah, so shall it be also in the days of the Son of man.

02:03:13.250 --> 02:03:19.870
They did eat, they drank, they married wives, they were given in marriage, until the day that

02:03:19.870 --> 02:03:28.350
Noah entered unto the ark, and the flood came and destroyed them all. Likewise also as it was

02:03:28.350 --> 02:03:35.550
in the days of Lot. They did eat, they drank, they bought, they sold, they planted, they builded.

02:03:36.530 --> 02:03:42.110
But the same day that Lot went out of Sodom, it rained fire and brimstone from heaven,

02:03:42.530 --> 02:03:48.870
and destroyed them all. Even thus shall it be in the day when the Son of man is revealed.

02:03:49.510 --> 02:03:55.050
In that day he which shall be upon the housetop, and his stuff in the house,

02:03:55.050 --> 02:04:01.750
let him not come down to take it away. And he that is in the field, let him likewise not return back.

02:04:02.610 --> 02:04:08.650
Remember Lot's wife. Whosoever shall seek to save his life shall lose it,

02:04:09.090 --> 02:04:15.890
and whosoever shall lose his life shall preserve it. I tell you, in that night

02:04:15.890 --> 02:04:21.910
there shall be two men in one bed, the one shall be taken, and the other shall be left.

02:04:22.690 --> 02:04:30.050
Two women shall be grinding together, the one shall be taken, and the other left. Two men shall

02:04:30.050 --> 02:04:37.990
be in the field, the one shall be taken, and the other left. And they answered and said unto him,

02:04:38.130 --> 02:04:46.310
Where, Lord? And he said unto them, Whosoever the body is, thither will the eagles be gathered

02:04:46.310 --> 02:04:57.450
together. And he spake a parable unto them to this end, that men ought always to pray

02:04:57.450 --> 02:05:06.470
and not to faint, saying, There was in a city a judge, which feared not God, neither regarded man.

02:05:07.430 --> 02:05:14.110
And there was a widow in that city, and she came unto him, saying, Avenge me of mine adversary.

02:05:15.050 --> 02:05:22.070
And he would not for a while, but afterward he said within himself, Though I fear not God nor

02:05:22.070 --> 02:05:29.030
regard men, yet because this widow troubleth me, I will avenge her, lest by her continual coming

02:05:29.030 --> 02:05:37.650
she weary me. And the Lord said, Hear what the unjust judge saith, And shall not God avenge

02:05:37.650 --> 02:05:44.090
his own elect, which cried day and night unto him, though he bear long with them? I tell you,

02:05:44.090 --> 02:05:51.010
that he will avenge them speedily. Nevertheless, when the Son of man cometh, shall he find faith

02:05:51.010 --> 02:05:57.510
on the earth? And he spake this parable unto certain which trusted in themselves that they

02:05:57.510 --> 02:06:04.850
were righteous and despised others. Two men went up into the temple to pray,

02:06:05.190 --> 02:06:12.270
the one a Pharisee and the other a publican. The Pharisee stood and prayed thus with himself,

02:06:13.070 --> 02:06:20.090
God, I thank thee that I am not as other men are extortioners, unjust, adulterers,

02:06:20.250 --> 02:06:26.870
or even as this publican. I fast twice in the week, I give tithes of all that I possess.

02:06:27.930 --> 02:06:35.130
And the publican standing afar off would not lift up so much as his eyes unto heaven,

02:06:35.630 --> 02:06:40.470
but smote upon his breast, saying, God, be merciful to me a sinner.

02:06:42.270 --> 02:06:49.590
I tell you, this man went down to his house justified rather than the other. For everyone

02:06:49.590 --> 02:06:55.590
that exalteth himself shall be abased, and he that humbleth himself shall be exalted.

02:06:56.730 --> 02:07:03.990
And they brought unto him also infants, that he would touch them. But when his disciples saw it,

02:07:03.990 --> 02:07:12.150
they rebuked them. But Jesus called them unto him and said, Suffer little children to come unto me,

02:07:12.150 --> 02:07:19.410
and forbid them not, for of such is the kingdom of God. Verily I say unto thee,

02:07:19.550 --> 02:07:25.530
whosoever shall not receive the kingdom of God as a little child shall in no wise enter therein.

02:07:26.930 --> 02:07:33.690
And a certain ruler asked him, saying, Good master, what shall I do to inherit eternal life?

02:07:34.990 --> 02:07:43.390
And Jesus said unto him, Why callest thou me good? None is good save one, that is God.

02:07:44.270 --> 02:07:49.710
Thou knowest the commandments, do not commit adultery, do not kill, do not steal,

02:07:50.070 --> 02:07:57.290
do not bear false witness, honor thy father and thy mother. And he said, All these I have kept

02:07:57.290 --> 02:08:05.730
from my youth up. Now when Jesus heard these things, he said unto him, Yet lackest thou one

02:08:05.730 --> 02:08:13.570
thing. Sell all that thou hast, and distribute unto the poor, and thou shalt have treasure in

02:08:13.570 --> 02:08:23.330
heaven. And come, follow me. And when he heard this, he was very sorrowful, for he was very rich.

02:08:24.390 --> 02:08:32.770
And when Jesus saw that he was very sorrowful, he said, How hardly shall they that have riches

02:08:32.770 --> 02:08:39.770
enter into the kingdom of God. For it is easier for a camel to go through a needle's eye,

02:08:40.050 --> 02:08:47.670
than for a rich man to enter into the kingdom of God. And they that heard it said, Who then can be

02:08:47.670 --> 02:08:55.190
saved? And he said, The things which are impossible with men are possible with God.

02:08:56.590 --> 02:09:05.970
Then Peter said, Lo, we have left all, and followed thee. And he said unto them, Verily I say unto

02:09:05.970 --> 02:09:11.850
you, There is no man that hath left house, or parents, or brethren, or wife, or children,

02:09:11.850 --> 02:09:17.790
for the kingdom of God's sake, who shall not receive manifold more in this present time,

02:09:18.170 --> 02:09:26.890
and in the world to come, life everlasting. Then he took unto him the twelve, and said unto them,

02:09:27.770 --> 02:09:33.450
Behold, we go up to Jerusalem, and all things that are written by the prophets concerning

02:09:33.450 --> 02:09:39.690
the Son of Man shall be accomplished. For he shall be delivered unto the Gentiles,

02:09:39.690 --> 02:09:47.590
and shall be mocked, and spitefully entreated, and spit it upon. And they shall scourge him,

02:09:47.830 --> 02:09:52.850
and put him to death, and the third day he shall rise again.

02:09:54.450 --> 02:10:01.830
And they understood none of these things, and this saying was hid from them, neither knew they the

02:10:01.830 --> 02:10:10.670
things which were spoken. And it came to pass, that as he was come nigh unto Jericho, a certain

02:10:10.670 --> 02:10:17.710
blind man sat by the wayside begging. And hearing the multitude pass by, he asked what it meant.

02:10:18.450 --> 02:10:25.970
And they told him that Jesus of Nazareth passeth by. And he cried, saying, Jesus, thou Son of David,

02:10:25.970 --> 02:10:33.330
have mercy on me. And they which went before rebuked him, that he should hold his peace.

02:10:33.790 --> 02:10:40.810
But he cried so much the more, thou Son of David, have mercy on me. And Jesus stood,

02:10:41.590 --> 02:10:47.190
and commanded him to be brought unto him. And when he was come near, he asked him, saying,

02:10:48.110 --> 02:10:55.770
What wilt thou that I shall do unto thee? And he said, Lord, that I may receive my sight,

02:10:56.890 --> 02:11:03.270
and Jesus said unto him, Receive thy sight, thy faith hath saved thee.

02:11:04.630 --> 02:11:10.270
And immediately he received his sight, and followed him, glorifying God,

02:11:10.870 --> 02:11:15.670
and all the people, when they saw it, gave praise unto God.

02:11:31.750 --> 02:11:36.450
Reading by Father Zeile of Detroit, December 2008.

02:11:55.296 --> 02:11:56.436
Version.

02:12:23.556 --> 02:12:29.656
And Jesus entered and passed through Jericho. And, behold, there was a man named Zacchaeus,

02:12:29.656 --> 02:12:36.176
which was the chief among the publicans, and he was rich. And he sought to see Jesus, who

02:12:36.176 --> 02:12:44.016
he was, and could not for the press, because he was little of stature. And he ran before

02:12:44.016 --> 02:12:49.456
and climbed up into a sycamore tree to see him, for he was to pass that way.

02:12:50.396 --> 02:12:56.616
And when Jesus came to the place, he looked up and saw him, and said unto him,

02:12:57.536 --> 02:13:03.776
Zacchaeus, make haste and come down, for today I must abide at thy house.

02:13:04.796 --> 02:13:11.896
And he made haste, and came down, and received him joyfully. And when they saw it, they all

02:13:11.896 --> 02:13:16.936
murmured, saying, that he was gone to beguessed with a man that is a sinner.

02:13:17.836 --> 02:13:24.656
And Zacchaeus stood and said unto the Lord, Behold, Lord, the half of my goods I give to

02:13:24.656 --> 02:13:31.476
the poor. And if I have taken anything from any man by false accusation, I restore him

02:13:31.476 --> 02:13:39.616
fourfold. And Jesus said unto him, This day is salvation come to this house, for as much

02:13:39.616 --> 02:13:46.796
as he also is a son of Abraham. For the son of man is come to seek and to save that which

02:13:46.796 --> 02:13:53.916
was lost. And as they heard these things, he added and spake a parable, because he was

02:13:53.916 --> 02:13:58.916
an eye to Jerusalem, and because they thought that the kingdom of God should immediately

02:13:58.916 --> 02:14:06.456
appear. He said therefore, A certain nobleman went into a far country to receive for himself

02:14:06.456 --> 02:14:13.576
a kingdom, and to return. And he called his ten servants, and delivered them ten pounds,

02:14:13.736 --> 02:14:21.456
and said unto them, Occupy till I come. But his citizens hated him, and sent a message

02:14:22.056 --> 02:14:28.516
saying, We will not have this man to reign over us. And it came to pass that when he

02:14:28.516 --> 02:14:34.096
was returned, having received the kingdom, then he commanded these servants to be called

02:14:34.096 --> 02:14:40.156
unto him, to whom he had given the money, that he might know how much every man had

02:14:40.156 --> 02:14:48.376
gained by trading. Then came the first, saying, Lord, thy pound hath gained ten pounds. And

02:14:48.376 --> 02:14:54.516
he said unto him, Well, thou good servant, because thou hast been faithful in a very

02:14:54.516 --> 02:15:01.956
little, have thou authority over ten cities. And the second came, saying, Lord, thy pound

02:15:01.956 --> 02:15:10.516
hath gained five pounds. And he said likewise to him, Be thou also over five cities. And

02:15:10.516 --> 02:15:16.556
another came, saying, Lord, behold, here is thy pound which I have kept laid up in a napkin.

02:15:17.116 --> 02:15:23.796
For I feared thee, because thou art an austere man. Thou takest up that which thou layest

02:15:23.796 --> 02:15:31.556
not down, and reapest that thou didst not sow. And he saith unto him, Out of thine own

02:15:31.556 --> 02:15:38.076
mouth will I judge thee, thou wicked servant. Thou knewest that I was an austere man, taking

02:15:38.076 --> 02:15:46.016
up that I laid not down, and reaping that I did not sow. Wherefore then gavest not thou

02:15:46.016 --> 02:15:53.476
my money into the bank, that at my coming I might have required my own with usury? And

02:15:53.476 --> 02:15:59.156
he said unto them that stood by, Take from him the pound, and give it to him that hath

02:15:59.156 --> 02:16:06.776
ten pounds. And they said unto him, Lord, he hath ten pounds. For I say unto you, that

02:16:06.776 --> 02:16:14.116
unto every one which hath shall be given, and from him that hath not, even that he hath

02:16:14.116 --> 02:16:20.596
shall be taken away from him. But those mine enemies, which would not that I should reign

02:16:20.596 --> 02:16:24.616
over them, bring hither, and slay them before me.

02:16:26.516 --> 02:16:33.756
And when he had thus spoken, he went before, ascending up to Jerusalem. And it came to

02:16:33.756 --> 02:16:39.836
pass, when he was come nigh to Bethphagy and Bethany, at the mount called the Mount of

02:16:39.836 --> 02:16:47.916
Olives, he sent two of his disciples, saying, Go ye into the village over against you, in

02:16:47.916 --> 02:16:54.856
the which at your entering ye shall find a colt tide, whereon, yet never man sat, loose

02:16:54.856 --> 02:17:02.156
him, and bring him hither. And if any man ask you, Why do ye loose him? thus shall ye

02:17:02.156 --> 02:17:05.776
say unto him, Because the Lord hath need of him.

02:17:06.736 --> 02:17:12.756
And they that were sent went their way, and found even as he had said unto them. And

02:17:12.756 --> 02:17:19.376
as they were loosing the colt, the owners thereof said unto them, Why loose ye the colt?

02:17:19.736 --> 02:17:26.576
And they said, The Lord hath need of him. And they brought him to Jesus. And they cast

02:17:26.576 --> 02:17:33.016
their garments upon the colt, and they set Jesus thereon. And as he went, they spread

02:17:33.016 --> 02:17:39.036
their clothes in the way. And when he was come nigh, even now, at the descent of the

02:17:39.036 --> 02:17:44.796
Mount of Olives, the whole multitude of the disciples began to rejoice and praise God

02:17:44.796 --> 02:17:50.556
with a loud voice for all the mighty works that they had seen, saying, Blessed be the

02:17:50.556 --> 02:17:55.856
King that cometh in the name of the Lord, Peace in heaven, and glory in the highest.

02:17:56.636 --> 02:18:03.176
And some of the Pharisees from among the multitude said unto him, Master, rebuke thy disciples.

02:18:04.176 --> 02:18:10.316
And he answered and said unto them, I tell you, that if these should hold their peace,

02:18:10.696 --> 02:18:16.896
the stones would immediately cry out. And when he was come near, he beheld the city

02:18:16.896 --> 02:18:25.396
and wept over it, saying, If thou hadst known even thou, at least in this thy day, the things

02:18:25.396 --> 02:18:32.036
which belong unto thy peace. But now they are hid from thine eyes. For the days shall

02:18:32.036 --> 02:18:37.996
come upon thee that thine enemies shall cast a trench about thee, and compass thee round,

02:18:38.436 --> 02:18:44.976
and keep thee in on every side, and shall lay thee even with the ground, and thy children

02:18:44.976 --> 02:18:51.996
within thee. And they shall not leave in thee one stone upon another, because thou knewest

02:18:51.996 --> 02:18:59.036
not the time of thy visitation. And he went into the temple, and began to cast out them

02:18:59.036 --> 02:19:06.136
that sold therein, and them that bought, saying unto them, It is written, My house is the

02:19:06.136 --> 02:19:13.536
house of prayer, but ye have made it a den of thieves. And he taught daily in the temple.

02:19:14.236 --> 02:19:19.416
But the chief priests and the scribes and the chief of the people sought to destroy

02:19:19.416 --> 02:19:25.796
him, and could not find what they might do, for all the people were very attentive to

02:19:25.796 --> 02:19:26.776
hear him.

02:19:27.816 --> 02:19:35.156
And it came to pass that on one of those days, as he taught the people in

02:19:35.156 --> 02:19:42.116
the temple, and preached the gospel, the chief priests and the scribes came upon him

02:19:42.116 --> 02:19:49.396
with the elders, and spake unto him, saying, Tell us, by what authority dost thou these

02:19:49.396 --> 02:19:57.956
things, or who is he that gave thee this authority? And he answered and said unto them, I will

02:19:57.956 --> 02:20:05.336
also ask you one thing, and answer me, The baptism of John, was it from heaven or of

02:20:05.336 --> 02:20:12.756
men? And they reasoned with themselves, saying, If we shall say from heaven, he will say,

02:20:13.136 --> 02:20:20.636
Why then believ ye him not? But and if we say of men, all the people will stone us,

02:20:20.836 --> 02:20:27.336
for they be persuaded that John was a prophet. And they answered that they could not tell

02:20:27.336 --> 02:20:35.796
whence it was. And Jesus said unto them, Neither tell I you by what authority I do these things.

02:20:36.556 --> 02:20:43.556
Then began he to speak to the people this parable. A certain man planted a vineyard

02:20:43.556 --> 02:20:51.376
and led it forth to husbandmen, and went into a far country for a long time. And at the

02:20:51.376 --> 02:20:57.356
season he sent a servant to the husbandmen that they should give him of the fruit of

02:20:57.356 --> 02:21:04.896
the vineyard. But the husbandmen beat him and sent him away empty. And again he sent

02:21:04.896 --> 02:21:10.936
another servant, and they beat him also, and entreated him shamefully, and sent him

02:21:10.936 --> 02:21:19.576
away empty. And again he sent a third, and they wounded him also, and cast him out. Then

02:21:19.576 --> 02:21:27.076
said the Lord of the vineyard, What shall I do? I will send my beloved son. It may be

02:21:27.076 --> 02:21:34.036
they will reverence him when they see him. But when the husbandmen saw him, they reasoned

02:21:34.036 --> 02:21:40.276
among themselves, saying, This is the heir. Come, let us kill him, that the inheritance

02:21:40.276 --> 02:21:48.036
may be ours. So they cast him out of the vineyard and killed him. What therefore shall the Lord

02:21:48.036 --> 02:21:53.556
of the vineyard do unto them? He shall come and destroy these husbandmen, and shall give

02:21:53.556 --> 02:21:59.836
the vineyard to others. And when they heard it, they said, God forbid. And he beheld them

02:21:59.836 --> 02:22:07.256
and said, What is this then that is written? The stone which the builders rejected, the

02:22:07.256 --> 02:22:13.976
same is become the head of the corner. Whosoever shall fall upon that stone shall be broken.

02:22:14.976 --> 02:22:22.956
But on whomsoever it shall fall, it will grind him to powder. And the chief priests and the

02:22:22.956 --> 02:22:29.216
scribes the same hour sought to lay hands on him, and they feared the people, for they

02:22:29.216 --> 02:22:36.276
perceived that he had spoken this parable against them. And they watched him, and sent

02:22:36.276 --> 02:22:42.096
forth spies which should feign themselves, just men, that they might take hold of his

02:22:42.096 --> 02:22:48.436
words, that so they might deliver him unto the power and authority of the governor. And

02:22:48.436 --> 02:22:55.276
they asked him, saying, Master, we know that thou sayest and teachest rightly, neither

02:22:55.276 --> 02:23:02.776
acceptest thou the person of any, but teachest the way of God truly. Is it lawful for us

02:23:02.776 --> 02:23:09.696
to give tribute unto Caesar, or no? But he perceived their craftiness, and said unto

02:23:09.696 --> 02:23:19.136
them, Why tempt ye me? show me a penny, whose image and superscription hath it? They answered

02:23:19.136 --> 02:23:26.556
and said, Caesar's. And he said unto them, Render therefore unto Caesar the things which

02:23:26.556 --> 02:23:33.576
be Caesar's, and unto God the things which be God's. And they could not take hold of

02:23:33.576 --> 02:23:39.716
his words before the people, and they marveled at his answer, and held their peace.

02:23:41.796 --> 02:23:47.536
Then came to him certain of the Sadducees, which deny that there is any resurrection,

02:23:47.536 --> 02:23:55.516
and they asked him, saying, Master, Moses wrote unto us, if any man's brother die having

02:23:55.516 --> 02:24:01.576
a wife, and he die without children, that his brother should take his wife and raise

02:24:01.576 --> 02:24:08.076
up seed unto his brother. There were therefore seven brethren, and the first took a wife,

02:24:08.396 --> 02:24:14.556
and died without children, and the second took her to wife, and he died childless, and

02:24:14.556 --> 02:24:20.776
the third took her, and in like manner the seven also, and they left no children, and

02:24:20.776 --> 02:24:27.876
died. Last of all the woman died also. Therefore in the resurrection whose wife of them is

02:24:27.876 --> 02:24:35.456
she? For seven had her to wife. And Jesus answering said unto them, The children of

02:24:35.456 --> 02:24:41.996
this world marry and are given in marriage. But they which shall be accounted worthy to

02:24:41.996 --> 02:24:48.336
obtain that world, and the resurrection from the dead, neither marry nor are given in marriage.

02:24:49.296 --> 02:24:55.876
Neither can they die any more, for they are equal unto the angels, and are the children

02:24:55.876 --> 02:25:03.476
of God, being the children of the resurrection. Now that the dead are raised, even Moses showed

02:25:03.476 --> 02:25:09.516
at the bush, when he called the Lord the God of Abraham, and the God of Isaac, and the

02:25:09.516 --> 02:25:17.176
God of Jacob. For he is not a God of the dead, but of the living, for all live unto him.

02:25:18.816 --> 02:25:27.116
Then certain of the scribes answering said, Master, thou hast well said. And after that

02:25:27.116 --> 02:25:35.736
they durst not ask him any questions at all. And he said unto them, How say they that Christ

02:25:35.736 --> 02:25:43.316
is David's son? And David himself saith in the book of Psalms, The Lord said unto my

02:25:43.316 --> 02:25:50.876
Lord, Sit thou on my right hand, till I make thine enemies thy footstool. David therefore

02:25:51.096 --> 02:25:59.476
calleth him Lord. How is he then his son? Then in the audience of all the people he

02:25:59.476 --> 02:26:07.436
said unto his disciples, Beware of the scribes which desire to walk in long robes, and love

02:26:07.436 --> 02:26:13.256
greetings in the markets, and the highest seats in the synagogues, and the chief rooms

02:26:13.256 --> 02:26:21.696
at feasts, which devour widows' houses, and for a show make long prayers. The same shall

02:26:21.696 --> 02:26:23.736
receive greater damnation.

02:27:06.658 --> 02:27:07.918
Authorized Version.

02:27:31.058 --> 02:27:36.298
And he looked up and saw the rich men

02:27:36.298 --> 02:27:43.718
their gifts into the treasury. And he saw also a certain poor widow casting in thither two

02:27:43.718 --> 02:27:51.478
mites. And he said, Of a truth, I say unto you, that this poor widow hath cast in more

02:27:51.478 --> 02:27:57.718
than they all. For all these have of their abundance cast in unto the offerings of God,

02:27:58.358 --> 02:28:02.758
but she of her penury hath cast in all the living that she had.

02:28:04.078 --> 02:28:10.638
And as some spake of the temple, how it was adorned with goodly stones and gifts, he said,

02:28:11.638 --> 02:28:18.698
As for these things which ye behold, the days will come in which there shall not be left one

02:28:18.698 --> 02:28:26.178
stone upon another, that shall not be thrown down. And they asked him, saying, Master,

02:28:26.558 --> 02:28:32.678
but when shall these things be, and what sign will there be when these things shall come to

02:28:32.678 --> 02:28:41.638
pass? And he said, Take heed that ye be not deceived, for many shall come in my name,

02:28:41.878 --> 02:28:50.398
saying, I am Christ, and the time draweth near. Go ye not therefore after them. But when ye shall

02:28:50.398 --> 02:28:57.658
hear of wars and commotions, be not terrified. For these things must first come to pass,

02:28:57.658 --> 02:29:06.358
but the end is not by and by. Then said he unto them, Nation shall rise against Nation,

02:29:06.778 --> 02:29:12.138
and Kingdom against Kingdom. And great earthquakes shall be in diverse places,

02:29:12.738 --> 02:29:20.558
and famines, and pestilences. And fearful sights and great signs shall there be from heaven. But

02:29:20.558 --> 02:29:27.638
before all these they shall lay their hands on you and persecute you, delivering you up to the

02:29:27.638 --> 02:29:34.438
synagogues, and into prisons, being brought before kings and rulers for my name's sake.

02:29:35.278 --> 02:29:42.858
And it shall turn to you for a testimony. Settle it therefore in your hearts, not to meditate before

02:29:42.858 --> 02:29:49.898
what ye shall answer. For I will give you a mouth and wisdom, which all your adversaries shall not

02:29:49.898 --> 02:29:57.618
be able to gainsay nor resist. And ye shall be betrayed both by parents and brethren, and kinsfolk's

02:29:57.618 --> 02:30:04.798
and friends. And some of you shall they cause to be put to death. And ye shall be hated of all men

02:30:04.798 --> 02:30:13.018
for my name's sake. But there shall not an hair of your head perish. In your patience possess ye

02:30:13.018 --> 02:30:20.018
your souls. And when ye shall see Jerusalem compassed with armies, then know that the

02:30:20.018 --> 02:30:27.598
desolation thereof is nigh. Then let them which are in Judea flee to the mountains. And let

02:30:27.598 --> 02:30:34.218
them which are in the midst of it depart out. And let not them that are in the countries enter

02:30:34.218 --> 02:30:41.918
there into. For these be the days of vengeance, that all things which are written may be fulfilled.

02:30:43.018 --> 02:30:49.758
But woe unto them that are with child, and to them that give suck in those days. For there

02:30:49.758 --> 02:30:56.558
shall be great distress in the land, and wrath upon this people. And they shall fall by the edge of

02:30:56.558 --> 02:31:03.898
sword, and shall be led away captive into all nations. And Jerusalem shall be trodden down of

02:31:03.898 --> 02:31:11.658
the Gentiles, until the times of the Gentiles be fulfilled. And there shall be signs in the sun,

02:31:11.898 --> 02:31:18.358
and in the moon, and in the stars, and upon the earth distress of nations with perplexity,

02:31:18.778 --> 02:31:25.318
the sea, and the waves roaring, men's hearts failing them for fear, and for looking after

02:31:25.318 --> 02:31:30.558
those things which are coming on the earth. For the powers of heaven shall be shaken.

02:31:31.398 --> 02:31:36.818
And then shall they see the Son of Man coming in a cloud with power and great glory.

02:31:37.638 --> 02:31:42.758
And when these things begin to come to pass, then look up and lift up your heads,

02:31:43.338 --> 02:31:49.178
for your redemption draweth nigh. And he spake to them a parable,

02:31:50.078 --> 02:31:57.198
Behold the fig tree and all the trees. When they now shoot forth, ye see and know of your own

02:31:57.198 --> 02:32:04.238
selves that summer is now nigh at hand. So likewise ye, when ye see these things come to pass,

02:32:04.638 --> 02:32:11.878
know ye that the kingdom of God is nigh at hand. Verily I say unto you, this generation shall not

02:32:11.878 --> 02:32:19.678
pass away till all be fulfilled. Heaven and earth shall pass away, but my words shall not pass away.

02:32:21.118 --> 02:32:27.558
And take heed to yourselves, lest at any time your hearts be overcharged with surfeiting

02:32:27.558 --> 02:32:34.378
and drunkenness and cares of this life, and so that day come upon you unawares.

02:32:35.018 --> 02:32:40.378
For as a snare shall it come on all them that dwell on the face of the whole earth.

02:32:40.938 --> 02:32:46.718
Watch ye therefore and pray always that ye may be accounted worthy to escape all these things

02:32:46.718 --> 02:32:53.338
that shall come to pass and to stand before the Son of Man. And in the daytime he was teaching

02:32:53.338 --> 02:33:00.338
in the temple, and at night he went out and abode in the mount that is called the Mount of Olives.

02:33:00.838 --> 02:33:06.498
And all the people came early in the morning to him in the temple for to hear him.

02:33:12.358 --> 02:33:17.078
Now the feast of unleavened bread drew nigh, which is called the Passover.

02:33:18.198 --> 02:33:23.938
And the chief priests and scribes sought how they might kill him, for they feared the people.

02:33:25.398 --> 02:33:31.678
Then entered Satan into Judas, surnamed Iscariot, being of the number of the twelve.

02:33:32.418 --> 02:33:39.438
And he went his way and communed with the chief priests and captains how he might betray him unto

02:33:39.438 --> 02:33:47.198
them. And they were glad and covenanted to give him money, and he promised and sought opportunity

02:33:47.198 --> 02:33:55.158
to betray him unto them in the absence of the multitude. Then came the day of unleavened bread,

02:33:55.158 --> 02:33:59.938
when the Passover must be killed. And he sent Peter and John, saying,

02:34:00.538 --> 02:34:04.138
Go and prepare us the Passover that we may eat.

02:34:05.638 --> 02:34:09.158
And they said unto him, Where wilt thou that we prepare?

02:34:09.898 --> 02:34:17.118
And he said unto them, Behold, when ye are entered into the city, there shall a man meet you,

02:34:17.238 --> 02:34:22.078
bearing a pitcher of water, follow him into the house where he entereth in.

02:34:22.718 --> 02:34:27.958
And ye shall say unto the goodman of the house, The master saith unto thee,

02:34:28.178 --> 02:34:33.358
Where is the guest chamber where I shall eat the Passover with my disciples?

02:34:33.918 --> 02:34:38.698
And he shall show you a large upper room furnished, there make ready.

02:34:40.138 --> 02:34:46.038
And they went and found as he had said unto them, and they made ready the Passover.

02:34:46.978 --> 02:34:52.898
And when the hour was come, he sat down, and the twelve apostles with him.

02:34:53.618 --> 02:35:01.258
And he said unto them, With desire I have desired to eat this Passover with you before I suffer,

02:35:01.958 --> 02:35:09.598
for I say unto you, I will not any more eat thereof until it be fulfilled in the kingdom of God.

02:35:10.998 --> 02:35:19.358
And he took the cup, and gave thanks, and said, Take this and divide it among yourselves,

02:35:20.198 --> 02:35:27.158
for I say unto you, I will not drink of the fruit of the vine until the kingdom of God shall come.

02:35:28.838 --> 02:35:36.058
And he took bread, and gave thanks, and break it, and gave it unto them, saying,

02:35:37.018 --> 02:35:43.898
This is my body which is given for you, this do in remembrance of me.

02:35:45.518 --> 02:35:53.198
Likewise also the cup after supper, saying, This cup is the New Testament in my blood,

02:35:53.718 --> 02:36:01.598
which is shed for you. But behold, the hand of him that betrayeth me is with me on the table.

02:36:02.758 --> 02:36:09.938
And truly the son of man goeth as it was determined, but woe unto that man by whom he is betrayed.

02:36:11.158 --> 02:36:16.578
And they began to inquire among themselves which of them it was that should do this thing.

02:36:17.998 --> 02:36:23.058
And there was also a strife among them which of them should be accounted the greatest.

02:36:23.658 --> 02:36:31.578
And he said unto them, The kings of the Gentiles exercise lordship over them, and they that exercise

02:36:31.578 --> 02:36:40.478
authority upon them are called benefactors. But ye shall not be so, but he that is greatest among

02:36:40.478 --> 02:36:48.378
you, let him be as the younger, and he that is chief, as he that doth serve it. For whether

02:36:48.378 --> 02:36:55.578
is greater, he that sitteth at meat, or he that serveth, is not he that sitteth at meat,

02:36:55.578 --> 02:37:03.558
but I am among you as he that serveth. Ye are they which have continued with me

02:37:03.558 --> 02:37:10.678
in my temptations, and I appoint unto you a kingdom, as my father hath appointed unto me,

02:37:11.318 --> 02:37:16.858
that ye may eat and drink at my table in my kingdom, and sit on thrones judging the

02:37:17.288 --> 02:37:27.278
of Israel. And the Lord said, Simon, Simon, behold, Satan hath desired to have you,

02:37:27.458 --> 02:37:33.398
that he may sift you as wheat, but I have prayed for thee that thy faith fail not,

02:37:34.038 --> 02:37:37.118
and when thou art converted strengthen thy brethren.

02:37:39.198 --> 02:37:45.258
And he said unto him, Lord, I am ready to go with thee both into prison and to death.

02:37:46.198 --> 02:37:51.618
And he said, I tell thee, Peter, the cock shall not crow this day,

02:37:51.858 --> 02:37:55.778
before that thou shalt trice deny that thou knowest me.

02:37:57.078 --> 02:38:03.298
And he said unto them, When I sent you without purse and scrip and shoes,

02:38:03.958 --> 02:38:11.938
lacked ye anything? And they said, Nothing. Then said he unto them, But now he that hath a

02:38:11.938 --> 02:38:18.018
purse, let him take it, likewise his scrip, and he that hath no sword, let him sell his garment

02:38:18.018 --> 02:38:24.898
and buy one, for I say unto you, that this that is written must be yet accomplished in me.

02:38:25.378 --> 02:38:31.558
And he was reckoned among the transgressors, for the things concerning me have an end.

02:38:32.618 --> 02:38:39.578
And they said, Lord, behold, here are two swords. And he said unto them, It is enough.

02:38:40.678 --> 02:38:49.138
And he came out and went as he was wont to the Mount of Olives, and his disciples also followed

02:38:49.138 --> 02:38:57.218
him. And when he was at the place, he said unto them, Pray that ye enter not into temptation.

02:38:58.858 --> 02:39:06.218
And he was withdrawn from them about a stone's cast and kneeled down and prayed, saying,

02:39:06.778 --> 02:39:15.078
Father, if thou be willing, remove this cup from me, nevertheless not my will but thine be done.

02:39:16.578 --> 02:39:23.578
And there appeared an angel unto him from heaven, strengthening him. And being in an agony,

02:39:24.458 --> 02:39:31.998
he prayed more earnestly, and his sweat was as it were great drops of blood falling down to the

02:39:31.998 --> 02:39:40.038
ground. And when he rose up from prayer and was come to his disciples, he found them sleeping

02:39:40.038 --> 02:39:48.678
for sorrow. And said unto them, Why sleep ye, rise and pray, lest ye enter into temptation.

02:39:49.478 --> 02:39:56.358
And while he yet spake, behold, a multitude, and he that was called Judas, one of the twelve,

02:39:56.358 --> 02:40:04.158
went before them, and drew near unto Jesus to kiss him. But Jesus said unto him, Judas,

02:40:04.978 --> 02:40:12.458
betrayest thou the son of man with a kiss? When they which were about him saw what would follow,

02:40:12.778 --> 02:40:26.338
they said unto him, Lord, shall we smite with the sword? And one of them smote the servant of the

02:40:26.338 --> 02:40:35.098
fire. And he touched his ear, and healed him. Then Jesus said unto the chief priests,

02:40:35.298 --> 02:40:42.318
and captains of the temple, and elders which were come to him, Be ye come out as against a thief

02:40:42.318 --> 02:40:49.038
with swords and staves? When I was daily with you in the temple, ye stretched forth no hands against

02:40:49.038 --> 02:40:57.498
me. But this is your hour, and the hour of darkness. Then took they him, and led him,

02:40:57.838 --> 02:41:04.838
and brought him into the high priest's house. And Peter followed afar off. And when they had

02:41:04.838 --> 02:41:11.278
kindled a fire in the midst of the hall, and were set down together, Peter sat down among them.

02:41:12.478 --> 02:41:18.938
But a certain maid beheld him as he sat by the fire, and earnestly looked upon him, and said,

02:41:19.038 --> 02:41:26.238
This man was also with him. And he denied him, saying, Woman, I know him not.

02:41:27.978 --> 02:41:34.818
And after a little while another saw him, and said, Thou art also of them. And Peter said,

02:41:34.938 --> 02:41:43.778
Man, I am not. And about the space of one hour after, another confidently affirmed, saying,

02:41:44.318 --> 02:41:51.738
Of a truth this fellow also was with him, for he is a Galilean. And Peter said, Man,

02:41:51.738 --> 02:41:57.418
I know not what thou sayest. And immediately while he yet spake, the cock crow.

02:41:58.518 --> 02:42:03.918
And the Lord turned and looked upon Peter, and Peter remembered the word of the Lord,

02:42:04.378 --> 02:42:10.478
how he had said unto him, Before the cock crow thou shalt deny me thrice.

02:42:11.278 --> 02:42:19.658
And Peter went out, and wept bitterly. And the man that held Jesus mocked him,

02:42:19.798 --> 02:42:26.038
and smote him. And when they had blindfolded him, they struck him on the face, and asked him,

02:42:26.478 --> 02:42:34.078
saying, Prophesy, who is it that smote thee? And many other things blasphemously spake they

02:42:34.078 --> 02:42:40.898
against him. And as soon as it was day, the elders of the people and the chief priests

02:42:40.898 --> 02:42:48.778
and the scribes came together, and led him into their counsel, saying, Art thou the Christ? Tell

02:42:48.778 --> 02:42:59.138
us. And he said unto them, If I tell you, he will not believe. And if I also ask you, he will not

02:42:59.138 --> 02:43:06.478
answer me, nor let me go. Hereafter shall the Son of Man sit on the right hand of the power of God.

02:43:07.378 --> 02:43:15.078
Then said they all, Art thou then the Son of God? And he said unto them, Ye say that I am.

02:43:15.878 --> 02:43:22.038
And they said, What need we any further witness? For we ourselves have heard of his own mouth.

02:43:31.038 --> 02:43:33.338
also known as the Authorized Version.

02:44:09.571 --> 02:44:13.031
READING BY FATHER ZILEY OF DETROIT

02:44:33.811 --> 02:44:37.831
And a whole multitude of them arose and led him on to Pilate.

02:44:38.111 --> 02:44:40.131
And they began to accuse him, saying,

02:44:40.471 --> 02:44:43.251
We found this fellow perverting the nation,

02:44:43.551 --> 02:44:45.551
and forbidding to give tribute to Caesar,

02:44:46.151 --> 02:44:49.071
saying that he himself is Christ, a King.

02:44:50.551 --> 02:44:52.491
And Pilate asked him, saying,

02:44:53.391 --> 02:44:55.111
Art thou the King of the Jews?

02:44:55.951 --> 02:44:57.771
And he answered him and said,

02:44:58.651 --> 02:44:59.991
Thou sayest it.

02:45:00.731 --> 02:45:04.031
Then said Pilate to the chief priests and to the people,

02:45:04.851 --> 02:45:06.891
I find no fault in this man.

02:45:07.911 --> 02:45:10.371
And they were the more fierce, saying,

02:45:10.691 --> 02:45:14.131
He stirth up the people, teaching throughout all Jewry,

02:45:14.411 --> 02:45:16.511
beginning from Galilee to this place.

02:45:17.811 --> 02:45:22.751
When Pilate heard of Galilee, he asked whether the man were a Galilean.

02:45:23.591 --> 02:45:28.271
And as soon as he knew that he belonged unto Herod's jurisdiction,

02:45:28.931 --> 02:45:34.431
he sent him to Herod, who himself also was at Jerusalem at that time.

02:45:35.971 --> 02:45:40.051
And when Herod saw Jesus, he was exceeding glad,

02:45:40.291 --> 02:45:44.051
for he was desirous to see him of a long season,

02:45:44.251 --> 02:45:46.751
because he had heard many things of him,

02:45:47.171 --> 02:45:50.651
and he hoped to have seen some miracle done by him.

02:45:51.711 --> 02:45:54.711
Then he questioned with him in many words,

02:45:55.251 --> 02:45:56.991
but he answered him nothing.

02:45:57.791 --> 02:46:02.171
And the chief priests and scribes stood and vehemently accused him.

02:46:03.371 --> 02:46:08.611
And Herod with his men of war set him at naught, and mocked him,

02:46:08.911 --> 02:46:13.491
and arrayed him in a gorgeous robe, and sent him again to Pilate.

02:46:14.571 --> 02:46:18.991
And the same day Pilate and Herod were made friends together,

02:46:19.931 --> 02:46:22.891
for before they were at enmity between themselves.

02:46:24.811 --> 02:46:29.551
And Pilate, when he had called together the chief priests and the rulers

02:46:29.551 --> 02:46:31.951
and the people, said unto them,

02:46:33.451 --> 02:46:37.691
Ye have brought this man unto me as one that perverteth the people.

02:46:38.231 --> 02:46:42.211
And behold, I, having examined him before you,

02:46:42.431 --> 02:46:47.251
have found no fault in this man touching those things, whereof ye accuse him.

02:46:47.831 --> 02:46:51.891
No, nor yet Herod, for I sent you to him,

02:46:52.351 --> 02:46:55.591
and lo, nothing worthy of death is done unto him.

02:46:55.591 --> 02:46:59.351
I will therefore chastise him and release him,

02:47:00.391 --> 02:47:05.111
for of necessity he must release one unto them at the feast.

02:47:05.931 --> 02:47:08.751
And they cried out all at once, saying,

02:47:09.171 --> 02:47:13.431
Away with this man, and release unto us Barabbas,

02:47:13.831 --> 02:47:19.971
who for a certain sedition made in the city and for murder was cast into prison.

02:47:21.251 --> 02:47:25.251
Pilate therefore, willing to release Jesus, spake again to them,

02:47:25.251 --> 02:47:30.151
but they cried, saying, Crucify him, crucify him.

02:47:31.391 --> 02:47:36.211
And he said unto them the third time, Why, what evil hath he done?

02:47:36.651 --> 02:47:42.951
I have found no cause of death in him, I will therefore chastise him and let him go.

02:47:43.591 --> 02:47:48.611
And they were instant with loud voices requiring that he might be crucified,

02:47:49.331 --> 02:47:53.651
and the voices of them and of the chief priests prevailed.

02:47:54.471 --> 02:47:58.751
And Pilate gave sentence, that it should be as they required.

02:47:59.771 --> 02:48:05.371
And he released unto them him that for sedition and murder was cast into prison,

02:48:05.751 --> 02:48:09.971
whom they had desired. But he delivered Jesus to their will.

02:48:10.991 --> 02:48:16.571
And as they led him away, they laid hold upon one Simon, a Cyrenian,

02:48:16.951 --> 02:48:21.451
coming out of the country, and on him they laid the cross,

02:48:21.451 --> 02:48:28.251
that he might bear it after Jesus. And there followed him a great company of people,

02:48:28.471 --> 02:48:32.091
and of women, which also bewailed and lamented him.

02:48:33.051 --> 02:48:40.531
But Jesus, turning unto them, said, Daughters of Jerusalem, weep not for me,

02:48:41.071 --> 02:48:46.751
but weep for yourselves and for your children. For behold, the days are coming,

02:48:46.751 --> 02:48:52.091
in the which they shall say, Blessed are the barren, and the wombs that never bear,

02:48:52.491 --> 02:48:58.191
and the paps which never gave suck. Then shall they begin to say to the mountains,

02:48:58.611 --> 02:49:05.911
Fall on us, and to the hills cover us. For if they do these things in a green tree,

02:49:06.351 --> 02:49:13.031
what shall be done in the dry? And there were also two other

02:49:14.151 --> 02:49:21.211
malefactors, led with him to be put to death. And when they were come to the place,

02:49:21.491 --> 02:49:27.391
which is called Calvary, there they crucified him, and the malefactors,

02:49:27.391 --> 02:49:30.891
one on the right hand, and the other on the left.

02:49:32.051 --> 02:49:39.311
Then said Jesus, Father, forgive them, for they know not what they do.

02:49:40.631 --> 02:49:48.151
And they parted his reinment, and cast lots, and the people stood beholding.

02:49:49.851 --> 02:49:56.611
And the rulers also with them derided him, saying, He saved others, let him save himself,

02:49:56.731 --> 02:50:03.011
if he be Christ, the Chosen of God. And the soldiers also mocked him,

02:50:03.011 --> 02:50:09.711
coming to him and offering him vinegar, and saying, If thou be the King of the Jews,

02:50:09.891 --> 02:50:17.191
save thyself. And a superscription also was written over him in letters of Greek,

02:50:17.691 --> 02:50:22.911
and Latin, and Hebrew, This is the King of the Jews.

02:50:24.691 --> 02:50:30.451
And one of the malefactors which were hanged railed on him, saying, If thou be Christ,

02:50:30.451 --> 02:50:36.891
save thyself and us. But the other answering rebuked him, saying,

02:50:37.751 --> 02:50:45.311
Dost not thou fear God, seeing thou art in the same condemnation? And we indeed justly,

02:50:45.431 --> 02:50:51.811
for we receive the due reward of our deeds. But this man hath done nothing amiss.

02:50:52.751 --> 02:50:59.391
And he said unto Jesus, Lord, remember me when thou comest into thy kingdom.

02:51:00.851 --> 02:51:09.951
And Jesus said unto him, Verily I say unto thee, Today shalt thou be with me in paradise.

02:51:12.151 --> 02:51:20.071
And it was about the sixth hour, and there was a darkness over all the earth until the ninth hour.

02:51:20.951 --> 02:51:26.231
And the sun was darkened, and the veil of the temple was rent in the midst.

02:51:26.231 --> 02:51:34.911
And when Jesus had cried with a loud voice, he said, Father, into thy hands I commend my

02:51:34.911 --> 02:51:46.811
spirit. And having said thus, he gave up the ghost. Now when the centurion saw what was done,

02:51:47.431 --> 02:51:55.051
he glorified God, saying, Certainly this was a righteous man. And all the people that came

02:51:55.051 --> 02:52:01.711
together to that site, beholding the things which were done, smote their breasts and returned.

02:52:03.871 --> 02:52:09.911
And all his acquaintance and the women that followed him from Galilee stood afar off,

02:52:10.391 --> 02:52:18.591
beholding these things. And behold, there was a man named Joseph, a counselor,

02:52:19.231 --> 02:52:27.811
and he was a good man and a just. The same had not consented to the council and deed of them,

02:52:28.351 --> 02:52:35.931
he was of Arimathea, a city of the Jews, who also himself waited for the kingdom of God.

02:52:37.191 --> 02:52:45.491
This man went on the pilot and begged the body of Jesus, and he took it down and wrapped it in linen

02:52:45.491 --> 02:52:53.151
and laid it in a sepulcher that was hewn in stone, wherein never man before was laid.

02:52:54.751 --> 02:53:01.531
And that day was the preparation, and the Sabbath drew on. And the women also,

02:53:01.951 --> 02:53:09.451
which came with him from Galilee, followed after and beheld the sepulcher and how his

02:53:09.451 --> 02:53:17.211
body was laid. And they returned and prepared spices and ointments and rested the Sabbath

02:53:17.211 --> 02:53:23.771
day according to the commandment

02:53:23.771 --> 02:53:31.331
Now upon the first day of the week, very early in the morning, they came unto the sepulcher,

02:53:31.831 --> 02:53:38.251
bringing the spices which they had prepared, and certain others with them. And they found

02:53:38.251 --> 02:53:44.671
the stone rolled away from the sepulcher. And they entered in, and found not the body

02:53:44.671 --> 02:53:51.491
of the Lord Jesus. And it came to pass, as they were much perplexed thereabout, behold,

02:53:51.971 --> 02:53:59.331
two men stood by them in shining garments. And as they were afraid, and bowed down their faces to

02:53:59.331 --> 02:54:06.991
the earth, they said unto them, Why seek ye the living among the dead? He is not here,

02:54:06.991 --> 02:54:13.851
but is risen. Remember how he spake unto you when he was yet in Galilee, saying,

02:54:14.131 --> 02:54:19.611
The son of man must be delivered into the hands of sinful men, and be crucified,

02:54:20.031 --> 02:54:27.851
and the third day rise again. And they remembered his words, and returned from the sepulcher,

02:54:28.411 --> 02:54:32.491
and told all these things unto the eleven, and to all the rest.

02:54:33.671 --> 02:54:42.131
It was Mary Magdalene, and Joanna, and Mary the mother of James, and other women that were with

02:54:42.131 --> 02:54:49.631
them, which told these things unto the apostles. And their words seemed to them as idle tales,

02:54:49.991 --> 02:54:57.331
and they believed them not. Then arose Peter, and ran unto the sepulcher, and stooping down,

02:54:57.331 --> 02:55:04.131
he beheld the linen clothes laid by themselves, and departed, wondering in himself

02:55:04.131 --> 02:55:11.911
at that which was come to pass. And behold, two of them went that same day to a village

02:55:11.911 --> 02:55:19.751
called Emmaus, which was from Jerusalem about three score furlongs, and they talked together

02:55:19.751 --> 02:55:27.151
of all these things which had happened. And it came to pass that while they communed together,

02:55:27.331 --> 02:55:36.491
and reasoned, Jesus himself drew near, and went with them. But their eyes were holden that they

02:55:36.491 --> 02:55:44.731
should not know him. And he said unto them, What manner of communications are these, that ye have

02:55:44.731 --> 02:55:52.571
one to another, as ye walk and are sad? And the one of them, whose name was Cleopas, answering,

02:55:52.571 --> 02:55:59.531
said unto him, Art thou only a stranger in Jerusalem, and hast not known the things

02:55:59.531 --> 02:56:06.631
which are come to pass there in these days? And he said unto them, What things?

02:56:07.631 --> 02:56:14.411
And they said unto him, Concerning Jesus of Nazareth, which was a prophet, mighty in deed

02:56:14.411 --> 02:56:20.651
and word before God and all the people, and how the chief priests and our rulers delivered him to

02:56:20.651 --> 02:56:28.551
condemn to death, and have crucified him. But we trusted that it had been he which should have

02:56:28.551 --> 02:56:36.371
redeemed Israel. And beside all this, today is the third day since these things were done.

02:56:37.211 --> 02:56:43.371
Yea, and certain women also of our company made us astonished which were early at the sepulcher.

02:56:44.071 --> 02:56:50.771
And when they found not his body, they came saying that they had also seen a vision of angels

02:56:50.771 --> 02:56:58.111
which said that he was alive. And certain of them which were with us went to the sepulcher

02:56:58.111 --> 02:57:03.571
and found it even so as the women had said, but him they saw not.

02:57:05.491 --> 02:57:12.691
Then he said unto them, O fools and slow of heart to believe all that the prophets have spoken.

02:57:13.371 --> 02:57:18.731
Ought not Christ to have suffered these things and to enter into his glory?

02:57:20.371 --> 02:57:26.831
And beginning at Moses and all the prophets, he expounded unto them in all the scriptures

02:57:26.831 --> 02:57:33.971
the things concerning himself. And they drew nigh unto the village whither they went,

02:57:34.591 --> 02:57:40.151
and he made as though he would have gone further. But they constrained him saying,

02:57:40.151 --> 02:57:49.691
Abide with us, for it is toward evening, and the day is far spent, and he went in to Terry with them.

02:57:50.571 --> 02:57:58.191
And it came to pass, as he sat at meet with them, he took bread, and blessed it,

02:57:59.091 --> 02:58:07.111
and break, and gave to them. And their eyes were opened, and they knew him,

02:58:08.131 --> 02:58:16.871
and he vanished out of their sight. And they said one to another, Did not our heart burn within us

02:58:16.871 --> 02:58:21.891
while he talked with us by the way, and while he opened to us the scriptures?

02:58:23.031 --> 02:58:29.971
And they rose up the same hour, and returned to Jerusalem, and found the eleven gathered together,

02:58:30.511 --> 02:58:37.091
and them that were with them, saying, The Lord is risen indeed, and hath appeared to some of us,

02:58:37.091 --> 02:58:45.411
Simon. And they told what things were done in the way, and how he was known of them

02:58:45.411 --> 02:58:54.271
in breaking of bread. And as they thus spake, Jesus himself stood in the midst of them,

02:58:54.711 --> 02:59:01.491
and saith unto them, Peace be unto you. But they were terrified, and affrighted,

02:59:01.491 --> 02:59:09.831
and supposed that they had seen a spirit. And he said unto them, Why are ye troubled?

02:59:10.331 --> 02:59:17.531
And why do thoughts arise in your hearts? Behold my hands and my feet, that it is I myself.

02:59:18.031 --> 02:59:24.471
Handle me, and see, for a spirit hath not flesh and bones, as ye see me have.

02:59:25.751 --> 02:59:33.251
And when he had thus spoken, he showed them his hands and his feet. And while they yet believed

02:59:33.251 --> 02:59:41.031
not for joy, and wondered, he said unto them, Have ye any meat? And they gave him a piece

02:59:41.031 --> 02:59:47.531
of a broiled fish, and of a honeycomb. And he took it, and did eat before them.

02:59:48.311 --> 02:59:55.571
And he said unto them, These are the words which I spake unto you while I was yet with you,

02:59:55.851 --> 03:00:01.591
that all things must be fulfilled which were written in the law of Moses, and in the prophets,

03:00:01.931 --> 03:00:09.711
and in the Psalms concerning me. Then opened he their understanding that they might understand

03:00:09.711 --> 03:00:18.251
the scriptures. And said unto them, Thus it is written, and thus it behoved Christ to suffer,

03:00:18.591 --> 03:00:25.331
and to rise from the dead the third day. And that repentance and remission of sins should be

03:00:25.331 --> 03:00:32.771
preached in his name among all nations, beginning at Jerusalem. And ye are witnesses of these things.

03:00:33.531 --> 03:00:40.631
And, behold, I send the promise of my Father upon you, but tarry ye in the city of Jerusalem

03:00:40.631 --> 03:00:50.071
until ye be endued with power from on high. And he led them out as far as to Bethany,

03:00:50.671 --> 03:00:57.591
and he lifted up his hands and blessed them. And it came to pass, while he blessed them,

03:00:57.591 --> 03:01:05.711
he was parted from them, and carried up into heaven. And they worshiped him, and returned

03:01:05.711 --> 03:01:14.831
to Jerusalem with great joy, and were continually in the temple, praising and blessing God. Amen.
